WEBVTT

1
00:02:48.900 --> 00:02:50.432
Yes, ma'am, how ya doin'?

2
00:02:50.495 --> 00:02:52.400
Is this Rose Hill?

3
00:02:52.500 --> 00:02:55.435
Good, This is Ed Couch.

4
00:02:55.500 --> 00:02:57.946
I'm Vesta Adcock's nephew.

5
00:02:58.003 --> 00:03:00.244
I need to get up there
and see her,

6
00:03:00.305 --> 00:03:04.310
but I'm gonna be late
'cause I'm lost out here.

7
00:03:04.376 --> 00:03:06.856
We're off the Alabama interstate
but I don't know where.

8
00:03:43.281 --> 00:03:47.195
- Did you hear that?
- What?

9
00:03:47.252 --> 00:03:49.323
The train.

10
00:03:49.387 --> 00:03:52.266
No, I didn't hear
no train.

11
00:03:54.025 --> 00:03:56.369
Oh, nothin',
I guess.

12
00:03:56.428 --> 00:04:00.843
- Where's "Whistle Stop" on the map?
- I can't find it.

13
00:04:00.899 --> 00:04:04.779
Why did you tell me to
turn right 10 miles back there?

14
00:04:06.304 --> 00:04:09.842
God, you got a negative
sense of direction, hon.

15
00:04:09.908 --> 00:04:12.787
I'm sorry.

16
00:04:12.844 --> 00:04:17.054
Oh, Ed,your aunt's gonna be
so disappointed we're late.

17
00:04:17.115 --> 00:04:21.120
I know she's been looking forward
to this visit all week long.

18
00:04:21.186 --> 00:04:24.463
Bless her sweet,
little ol' heart.

19
00:04:28.593 --> 00:04:31.472
Hey, how's my sweet Auntie V
this afternoon?

20
00:04:31.529 --> 00:04:34.135
Remember us?

21
00:04:34.199 --> 00:04:37.271
- Don't you look pretty!
- We brought you something.

22
00:04:37.335 --> 00:04:40.509
- Let me look at you.

23
00:04:40.572 --> 00:04:43.178
Don't you know
Evelyn loves you?

24
00:04:43.241 --> 00:04:48.088
Well, honey, I guess it'd be
better if you wait out here for me.

25
00:04:48.146 --> 00:04:52.617
- I'll get all this stuff.
- Well, if you think it's best.

26
00:04:52.684 --> 00:04:55.995
Yeah, I do this time.
Okay?

27
00:04:56.054 --> 00:04:58.227
Have a nice day,
Aunt Vesta.

28
00:04:58.290 --> 00:05:00.236
Don't you pitch a fit
like that'

29
00:05:12.203 --> 00:05:14.911
Did you know
they took my gallbladder out?

30
00:05:16.341 --> 00:05:18.480
No, I didn't.

31
00:05:18.543 --> 00:05:22.218
Oh, yes. Still
in the hospital in ajar.

32
00:05:22.280 --> 00:05:27.093
I guess that's where
they keep 'em.

33
00:05:27.152 --> 00:05:29.132
I guess.

34
00:05:29.187 --> 00:05:31.428
When I was
in the hospital,

35
00:05:31.489 --> 00:05:35.460
the nurse gave me one of them
Fleet enemas they're so fond of.

36
00:05:35.527 --> 00:05:38.133
Mrs. Cleo Threadgoode,

37
00:05:38.196 --> 00:05:41.507
82 year old widow,
imagine that.

38
00:05:41.566 --> 00:05:44.706
Actually,
everybody calls me Ninny.

39
00:05:44.769 --> 00:05:47.010
'Course I'm
just visitin' here.

40
00:05:47.072 --> 00:05:52.351
Did you ever have
one of them Fleet enemas?

41
00:05:52.410 --> 00:05:54.356
Um,well?

42
00:05:54.412 --> 00:05:56.483
No.

43
00:05:56.548 --> 00:05:59.791
You'd remember it.

44
00:05:59.851 --> 00:06:03.526
Me and my friend, Mrs. Otis,
come from Whistle Stop.

45
00:06:03.588 --> 00:06:05.795
You ever been
to Whistle Stop?

46
00:06:05.857 --> 00:06:09.270
Why, yes. I just
passed by there today.

47
00:06:09.327 --> 00:06:14.208
She's lived down the street
from me for 30 years or more.

48
00:06:14.265 --> 00:06:16.267
After her son died,

49
00:06:16.334 --> 00:06:19.941
her daughter-in-law had a fit for
her to come live at the nursing home.

50
00:06:20.004 --> 00:06:23.315
They asked me to come
and be her roommate.

51
00:06:23.375 --> 00:06:27.619
Mrs. Otis don't know it, but I'm going
home just soon as she gets settled in good.

52
00:06:29.948 --> 00:06:33.361
Does the name "Idgie
Threadgoode" ring a bell?

53
00:06:33.418 --> 00:06:36.956
Um, no, ma'am.
I don't think so.

54
00:06:37.021 --> 00:06:39.831
You'd remember her.

55
00:06:39.891 --> 00:06:43.805
You see, I was practically
adopted by the Threadgoode family.

56
00:06:43.862 --> 00:06:46.206
- I married her brother, Cleo.
- Oh, uh-huh.

57
00:06:46.264 --> 00:06:51.043
Idgie and her friend Ruth,
ran the Whistle Stop Cafe.

58
00:06:51.102 --> 00:06:53.048
Oh.

59
00:06:53.104 --> 00:06:55.812
Idgie was a character,
all right.

60
00:06:55.874 --> 00:06:59.219
But how anybody
could've thought...

61
00:06:59.277 --> 00:07:03.316
she murdered that man
is beyond me.

62
00:07:03.381 --> 00:07:05.361
I beg your pardon?

63
00:07:05.417 --> 00:07:08.990
You sit and relax a while.
I'll tell you all about it.

64
00:07:09.053 --> 00:07:11.693
Oh, now, let's see.

65
00:07:11.756 --> 00:07:15.226
I 'member the day they pulled
that truck up out of the river.

66
00:07:15.293 --> 00:07:19.264
That same rainy
summer day...

67
00:07:19.330 --> 00:07:24.279
Idgie Threadgoode was arrested for
the murder of the owner of that truck,

68
00:07:24.335 --> 00:07:27.316
Frank Bennett.

69
00:07:29.607 --> 00:07:32.053
I guess,
to understand Idgie,

70
00:07:32.110 --> 00:07:35.819
you'd have to start way back
with her brother, Buddy.

71
00:07:35.880 --> 00:07:40.829
Idgie was Buddy's pet
from the day she was born.

72
00:07:43.221 --> 00:07:46.998
I 'member the day we was all
gettin' ready for Leona's weddin'.

73
00:07:47.058 --> 00:07:49.038
The war had just ended,

74
00:07:49.093 --> 00:07:51.437
the Great one,
you know.

75
00:07:51.496 --> 00:07:56.172
And another one was about to
begin in the Threadgoode house.

76
00:07:56.234 --> 00:07:58.680
Sipsey hone )4
is that finished?

77
00:08:00.238 --> 00:08:03.185
- Buddy, get dressed honey.
- Mama?

78
00:08:03.241 --> 00:08:05.221
Leona, what is it?

79
00:08:05.276 --> 00:08:07.153
Idgie's upstairs
in her room...

80
00:08:07.212 --> 00:08:09.192
and says she won't come out
as long as she lives.

81
00:08:09.247 --> 00:08:11.386
- She is gonna ruin my weddin'!
- Shh.

82
00:08:11.449 --> 00:08:14.259
Leona, you're gonna be
the most beautiful bride.

83
00:08:14.319 --> 00:08:17.596
Of course she is, Papa.

84
00:08:17.655 --> 00:08:21.603
Your papa has spent every last
nickel he has just to make you happy.

85
00:08:21.659 --> 00:08:25.471
Now, you try to act
a little grateful, young lady.

86
00:08:25.530 --> 00:08:28.636
Imogene Louise Threadgoode!

87
00:08:28.700 --> 00:08:31.237
This is your mama!

88
00:08:33.638 --> 00:08:38.587
You come down here right now.
Do you hear me?

89
00:08:38.643 --> 00:08:41.283
- Buddy, fetch her. She'll listen to you.
- Come on down, little bit.

90
00:08:41.346 --> 00:08:43.917
There's no firin'
squad waitin' for you.

91
00:08:43.982 --> 00:08:49.330
Ohh! Come on, honey
Let us see you.

92
00:08:49.387 --> 00:08:51.560
You look so pretty.

93
00:08:51.623 --> 00:08:54.467
- I see London,
I see- - Hush!

94
00:08:56.194 --> 00:08:59.641
Julian, hush.

95
00:08:59.697 --> 00:09:02.439
Come ahead, sweetheart.

96
00:09:02.500 --> 00:09:06.243
You look awful nice
in that.

97
00:09:06.304 --> 00:09:07.908
- Mama!
- You look fine.

98
00:09:07.972 --> 00:09:10.475
She looks like a monkey

99
00:09:10.542 --> 00:09:12.351
Julian, stop it
right this second!

100
00:09:12.410 --> 00:09:15.755
Take it back! Take it back! Idgie, hey!

101
00:09:15.813 --> 00:09:18.919
I told you she
was gonna ruin my weddin'!

102
00:09:18.983 --> 00:09:21.361
- Idgie, get up.
- Take it back!

103
00:09:21.419 --> 00:09:23.592
Take it back!

104
00:09:23.655 --> 00:09:27.000
- I'll get you for this.
- No, Buddy.

105
00:09:30.795 --> 00:09:33.867
We have to be careful
when she's dressing up.

106
00:09:33.932 --> 00:09:35.878
She's just a pain!

107
00:09:35.934 --> 00:09:39.472
Leona, will you
stop shrieking'

108
00:09:39.537 --> 00:09:42.245
This is your
weddin ' day'

109
00:09:53.251 --> 00:09:56.095
I oaks like you got yourself
up a tree, little bit.

110
00:09:56.154 --> 00:09:59.192
I'm sick of people
makin' fun of me.

111
00:09:59.257 --> 00:10:01.794
So you're gonna stay up here
all day long.

112
00:10:01.859 --> 00:10:05.068
Yep.
The hell with them.

113
00:10:05.129 --> 00:10:09.077
Who wants to wear
that stupid ol' dress anyway?

114
00:10:09.133 --> 00:10:12.512
- I ever tell you about the oysters?
- Oysters?

115
00:10:12.570 --> 00:10:14.516
- I tell you about the oysters?
- No.

116
00:10:14.572 --> 00:10:19.248
Think about the millions of
oysters lyin' around the ocean.

117
00:10:19.310 --> 00:10:21.654
Then one day...

118
00:10:21.713 --> 00:10:24.523
God comes along and sees one
and he says,

119
00:10:24.582 --> 00:10:27.495
"I think I'm gonna make
that one different."

120
00:10:27.552 --> 00:10:29.759
You know what he does?

121
00:10:29.821 --> 00:10:32.995
He puts a little
piece of sand in it.

122
00:10:33.057 --> 00:10:37.301
- Guess what it can do that the others can't.
- What?

123
00:10:37.362 --> 00:10:40.673
It can make
a beautiful pearl.

124
00:10:40.732 --> 00:10:42.905
What if God
made a mistake?

125
00:10:42.967 --> 00:10:48.076
Well, the way I figure it,
he never makes mistakes.

126
00:10:48.139 --> 00:10:50.915
I mean, he made sure
we got together.

127
00:10:50.975 --> 00:10:52.977
He made sure you got
the best looking,

128
00:10:53.044 --> 00:10:55.251
most charmin' brother
in the world...

129
00:10:55.313 --> 00:10:58.692
- who's gonna beat you to the chocolate cake.
- You will not.

130
00:10:58.750 --> 00:11:01.128
Got you out of the tree,
didn't I?

131
00:11:01.185 --> 00:11:04.132
Did not!

132
00:11:04.188 --> 00:11:07.829
Into this estate,
these two come now to be joined

133
00:11:07.892 --> 00:11:09.997
If any man present
can show cause...

134
00:11:10.061 --> 00:11:12.473
why they may not lawfully
be joined together,

135
00:11:12.530 --> 00:11:17.673
let him speak now or
forever after hold his peace.

136
00:11:17.735 --> 00:11:20.409
Please be seated.

137
00:11:22.774 --> 00:11:24.981
If either of you
know any reason...

138
00:11:25.043 --> 00:11:28.024
why you may not justly be
joined together in holy matrimony

139
00:11:28.079 --> 00:11:30.559
do you now confess it?

140
00:11:40.191 --> 00:11:42.899
It is then your will
to proceed.

141
00:11:42.960 --> 00:11:46.669
Do you,
Charles Osgood justice-

142
00:11:52.503 --> 00:11:55.848
Thank you. I don't know what
we'd do without your generosity.

143
00:11:55.907 --> 00:11:58.888
Sipsey, especially you.
Look what you've clone!

144
00:11:58.943 --> 00:12:02.891
Thank you, Mrs. Threadgoode.
Gimme that, you rascal!

145
00:12:07.218 --> 00:12:09.789
John!
Jump on my back

146
00:12:09.854 --> 00:12:13.495
I don't think there ever was a
sweeter boy than Buddy Threadgoode.

147
00:12:13.558 --> 00:12:18.064
- You look beautiful, Lily.
- Yes, Lily, you sure do.

148
00:12:18.129 --> 00:12:21.576
I had the biggest crush
on him.

149
00:12:21.632 --> 00:12:23.976
He was a terrible flirt!

150
00:12:24.035 --> 00:12:27.278
But his heart belonged
to Ruth Jamison.

151
00:12:27.338 --> 00:12:30.512
She was the daughter of
a friend of his mama's...

152
00:12:30.575 --> 00:12:33.385
who was visitin'
that summer.

153
00:12:33.444 --> 00:12:36.914
Ruth Jamison, you're just
the one I've been lookin' for.

154
00:12:36.981 --> 00:12:40.087
- Are you thirsty?
- Let's go visit someplace else.

155
00:12:45.990 --> 00:12:49.335
Think that's a big lake, you should've
seen the one next to our house.

156
00:12:49.393 --> 00:12:51.532
We used to swim in it
and fish.

157
00:12:51.596 --> 00:12:54.270
I sure do miss it.
Sure do.

158
00:12:54.332 --> 00:12:57.074
What happened to it?
Did it dry up?

159
00:12:57.135 --> 00:12:59.081
No, worse than that.

160
00:12:59.137 --> 00:13:01.208
Last fall, a flock of ducks,

161
00:13:01.272 --> 00:13:05.550
40 or 50 of 'em, landed right
smack in the middle of it.

162
00:13:05.610 --> 00:13:07.487
This fluke thing
happened.

163
00:13:07.545 --> 00:13:10.025
The temperature dropped so fast
that the whole lake froze...

164
00:13:10.081 --> 00:13:12.083
in three seconds,
just like that!

165
00:13:12.150 --> 00:13:14.460
Those poor little ducks.
Did it kill them?

166
00:13:14.519 --> 00:13:17.728
No, they flew off
and took the lake with 'em.

167
00:13:17.789 --> 00:13:21.168
To this very day, that lake
is somewhere over in Georgia.

168
00:13:21.225 --> 00:13:24.672
Buddy Threadgoode.

169
00:13:35.640 --> 00:13:38.985
Come a little closer.
I wanna give you something.

170
00:13:39.043 --> 00:13:41.489
Come here.

171
00:13:45.349 --> 00:13:47.590
Whoop!

172
00:13:51.722 --> 00:13:55.135
Come back here, hat. Where
do you think you're gain'?

173
00:13:57.361 --> 00:13:59.307
Whoa!

174
00:13:59.363 --> 00:14:02.469
I got it. Hold on, Ruth.
Hold on, little bit.

175
00:14:06.871 --> 00:14:09.613
It's all right.
I got it.

176
00:14:11.742 --> 00:14:15.485
Come here, you damn hat. Got it!

177
00:14:15.546 --> 00:14:18.493
Oh, I meant
to do that.

178
00:14:19.550 --> 00:14:23.293
I... got it!

179
00:14:23.354 --> 00:14:25.231
Ta-da!

180
00:14:27.024 --> 00:14:29.561
All right.
Damn!

181
00:14:29.627 --> 00:14:31.607
Come on.

182
00:14:38.236 --> 00:14:43.117
Come on. Get out.
Get out.

183
00:14:43.174 --> 00:14:45.120
Buddy!

184
00:14:45.176 --> 00:14:48.419
- Buddy!
- Buddy Threadgoode!

185
00:14:50.047 --> 00:14:51.754
Come on, Buddy!

186
00:14:51.816 --> 00:14:53.557
Get out.

187
00:14:55.019 --> 00:14:57.158
Get out of there.

188
00:14:58.489 --> 00:15:02.301
Buddy!

189
00:15:02.360 --> 00:15:05.500
- Come on, Buddy!
- Buddy'

190
00:15:05.563 --> 00:15:08.169
Buddy!

191
00:15:10.701 --> 00:15:13.307
No-o-o!

192
00:15:13.371 --> 00:15:17.217
Buddy!

193
00:15:17.275 --> 00:15:20.688
Buddy, no!
No!

194
00:15:20.745 --> 00:15:23.521
No! Buddy!
No-o-o!

195
00:15:23.581 --> 00:15:26.619
No! Buddy!
Let me go!

196
00:15:28.085 --> 00:15:31.897
' No!
- Buddy!

197
00:15:31.956 --> 00:15:35.597
- You got to go back to the house.

198
00:15:35.660 --> 00:15:38.163
Come on.
We're gonna go home.

199
00:15:38.229 --> 00:15:41.073
- Buddy!
- You have to be strong.

200
00:15:41.132 --> 00:15:44.045
- It'll be okay.
- Buddy!

201
00:15:44.101 --> 00:15:47.048
"The Lord is my Shepherd,

202
00:15:47.104 --> 00:15:49.311
I shall not want."

203
00:15:49.373 --> 00:15:52.377
Oh, it like
to have killed us all

204
00:15:52.443 --> 00:15:55.117
But nary a one took it
as hard as Idgie,

205
00:15:58.215 --> 00:16:03.688
everyone thought she 'o' die
right along with him.

206
00:16:20.338 --> 00:16:24.616
Night alter night,
she stayed by the river.

207
00:16:24.675 --> 00:16:28.851
Big George was the only soul
she'd let near her,

208
00:16:28.913 --> 00:16:32.451
and he watched over her
night and day

209
00:16:32.516 --> 00:16:35.326
You know,
a heart can be broken,

210
00:16:35.386 --> 00:16:38.458
but it still keeps a-beatin'
just the same.

211
00:16:38.522 --> 00:16:41.162
Miss Idgie, you'll have
to keep this blanket on...

212
00:16:41.225 --> 00:16:44.138
or you'll catch your death
of cold, you hear me now?

213
00:16:44.195 --> 00:16:48.610
That's so sad.

214
00:16:54.005 --> 00:16:56.611
Ah.

215
00:16:56.674 --> 00:16:58.676
Would you like
one of these?

216
00:16:58.743 --> 00:17:00.745
Oh, thank ya,
honey.

217
00:17:00.811 --> 00:17:02.688
Evelyn?

218
00:17:02.747 --> 00:17:04.920
Honey,
we gotta get goin'.

219
00:17:04.982 --> 00:17:07.394
The Braves' game's
fixin' to start...

220
00:17:07.451 --> 00:17:09.089
and you're gonna miss
your... thing.

221
00:17:09.153 --> 00:17:12.896
Excuse me.
That's my husband, Ed.

222
00:17:12.957 --> 00:17:15.028
Hi, ma'am.
How you doin'?

223
00:17:15.092 --> 00:17:18.539
Um.

224
00:17:18.596 --> 00:17:20.667
I can't believe
Buddy died.

225
00:17:20.731 --> 00:17:23.337
Neither could I.

226
00:17:23.401 --> 00:17:26.814
Oh, well, I enjoyed
talkin' to you, honey.

227
00:17:26.871 --> 00:17:28.873
What's your name?

228
00:17:28.939 --> 00:17:32.011
Evelyn...
Evelyn Couch.

229
00:17:32.076 --> 00:17:36.855
- I've got to go.
- You come back and see me, you hear?

230
00:17:36.914 --> 00:17:40.828
- Okay.
- Bye-bye.

231
00:17:41.018 --> 00:17:43.294
First of all,
I want you...

232
00:17:43.354 --> 00:17:45.960
to truly
dedicate yourselves...

233
00:17:46.023 --> 00:17:50.062
to finding little ways to
putting that magic, that spark...

234
00:17:50.127 --> 00:17:52.334
back into your marriage.

235
00:17:52.396 --> 00:17:56.344
When we think of
romance and marriage,

236
00:17:56.400 --> 00:18:00.439
- what is the first thought that comes into your mind?
- Divorce!

237
00:18:00.504 --> 00:18:04.213
Remember when counselors used to tell
you to wrap yourself in cellophane...

238
00:18:04.275 --> 00:18:06.482
to put a little charge
into your marriage?

239
00:18:06.544 --> 00:18:09.354
Do we really pay
for these lectures?

240
00:18:09.413 --> 00:18:12.121
You can see,
it is truly up to you...

241
00:18:12.183 --> 00:18:15.687
to put romance back
into your relationship.

242
00:18:43.380 --> 00:18:45.360
Evelyn,
have you gone insane?

243
00:18:45.416 --> 00:18:47.362
My God
people can see you!

244
00:18:47.418 --> 00:18:49.489
What if I had been
the paperboy?

245
00:18:49.553 --> 00:18:51.328
Get in there!

246
00:18:51.388 --> 00:18:54.198
What are you
thinking about?

247
00:18:54.992 --> 00:18:58.337
Evelyn?

248
00:18:58.395 --> 00:19:00.705
- Evelyn!
- Oh.

249
00:19:00.764 --> 00:19:04.735
You know, what we really need
instead of this baloney...

250
00:19:04.802 --> 00:19:08.875
is an assertiveness training
class for Southern women.

251
00:19:08.939 --> 00:19:12.512
But that's a contradiction
in terms, isn't it?

252
00:19:12.576 --> 00:19:15.819
Especially you, sweetheart.
You're livin' in the Dark Ages.

253
00:19:39.069 --> 00:19:41.675
- Hi, honey. I need one of those.
- Hi!

254
00:19:41.739 --> 00:19:44.515
Mmm, you smell good too.

255
00:19:44.575 --> 00:19:46.612
I need one of these.

256
00:19:46.677 --> 00:19:49.624
- Oh, this looks good!
- Uh-huh.

257
00:19:49.680 --> 00:19:51.626
Yes, indeedy.

258
00:20:00.791 --> 00:20:03.772
Ed.

259
00:20:05.462 --> 00:20:07.635
Why don't you come in?
and sit down at the table...

260
00:20:07.698 --> 00:20:11.646
- and have dinner with me?
- I'm sorry. The game's almost over.

261
00:20:11.702 --> 00:20:14.546
I just want to see a little bit
of it. Why you so dressed up?

262
00:20:14.605 --> 00:20:17.108
Honey, don't get in the way.
Scoot over a bit.

263
00:20:21.245 --> 00:20:22.815
Ed?

264
00:20:22.880 --> 00:20:25.884
If I'd answered the door
wearing only cellophane,

265
00:20:25.950 --> 00:20:29.261
would you still be
watching the baseball game?

266
00:20:29.320 --> 00:20:33.063
No, honey. I'd probably be
checking you into a looney bin.

267
00:20:55.379 --> 00:20:59.623
Hi, sugar.

268
00:20:59.683 --> 00:21:01.629
- How's my dumplin'?
- Trick or treat!

269
00:21:01.685 --> 00:21:03.631
You 're not gonna throw
them hissy-fits, are you?

270
00:21:03.687 --> 00:21:06.930
Happy Halloween!
Oh, no. No, no, no!

271
00:21:06.991 --> 00:21:09.096
You 're meaner
than a damn snake.

272
00:21:09.159 --> 00:21:11.161
I'm glad
you're feeling better.

273
00:21:11.228 --> 00:21:14.471
- Get back in bed
- Good thing your eyesight's failing.

274
00:21:24.108 --> 00:21:27.248
- Hey!
- Mmm. Oh.

275
00:21:27.311 --> 00:21:30.724
- Hey.
- I was hopin' you'd be here.

276
00:21:30.781 --> 00:21:34.854
My roommate, Mrs. Otis,
said I could visit her family,

277
00:21:34.918 --> 00:21:36.864
but I said,
"Thank you kindly,

278
00:21:36.920 --> 00:21:39.560
but I think I might have
my own visitor."

279
00:21:39.623 --> 00:21:41.625
And here you are.

280
00:21:41.692 --> 00:21:43.968
- Well, sit down.
- Thank you.

281
00:21:44.028 --> 00:21:47.566
And doughnuts to boot!
You can't beat that.

282
00:21:47.631 --> 00:21:50.475
- Well, help yourself, Mrs. Threadgoode.
- Thank you.

283
00:21:51.201 --> 00:21:52.236
How's your friend?

284
00:21:52.303 --> 00:21:54.305
- Mrs. Otis?
- Uh-huh.

285
00:21:54.371 --> 00:21:57.318
- Well, not so good.
- Oh.

286
00:21:57.374 --> 00:22:00.116
Looks like I won't be
gettin' home for quite a while,

287
00:22:00.177 --> 00:22:03.624
and I sure miss it.

288
00:22:03.681 --> 00:22:06.958
Funny what you miss
when you're away from home.

289
00:22:07.017 --> 00:22:09.429
I miss
the smell of coffee...

290
00:22:09.486 --> 00:22:12.296
and bacon fryin'.

291
00:22:12.356 --> 00:22:16.862
Oh, what I wouldn't give for a
plate of fried green tomatoes...

292
00:22:16.927 --> 00:22:19.635
like we used to have
at the cafe.

293
00:22:19.697 --> 00:22:22.109
Ooh!

294
00:22:25.636 --> 00:22:28.708
I never told you about the cafe, did I?

295
00:22:28.772 --> 00:22:30.718
No, ma'am.

296
00:22:30.774 --> 00:22:35.382
Oh, well...
now let me back up a bit.

297
00:22:35.446 --> 00:22:40.691
You see, Idgie never
quite got over losing Buddy.

298
00:22:43.020 --> 00:22:46.092
She hardly
ever come home.

299
00:22:46.156 --> 00:22:49.035
Only Big George
knew how to find her.

300
00:22:49.093 --> 00:22:53.838
She just didn't seem to care
about anythin' anymore.

301
00:22:53.897 --> 00:22:55.843
Then, one summer day

302
00:22:55.899 --> 00:22:58.880
her mama sent for her.

303
00:22:58.936 --> 00:23:00.882
Like they say

304
00:23:00.938 --> 00:23:04.442
God never shuts one door
without opening another.

305
00:23:04.508 --> 00:23:08.149
- That was also the day Idgie met Frank Bennett,
- Mama!

306
00:23:08.212 --> 00:23:10.954
The man whose murder
got her arrested

307
00:23:11.014 --> 00:23:15.053
Well, hello there, miss.
And who might you be?

308
00:23:16.120 --> 00:23:18.623
Towanda to you.
Who are you?

309
00:23:18.689 --> 00:23:22.933
Oh, Frank Bennett's
the name, Miss Towanda.

310
00:23:22.993 --> 00:23:26.998
I must say you are lookin'
mighty fine today.

311
00:23:27.064 --> 00:23:29.066
You a politician...

312
00:23:29.133 --> 00:23:32.342
or does lying
just run in your family?

313
00:23:33.670 --> 00:23:36.344
Mama!

314
00:23:36.407 --> 00:23:38.284
Well, there you are!

315
00:23:38.342 --> 00:23:41.346
Well, it's about time,
Idgie.

316
00:23:44.148 --> 00:23:47.061
If you don't look like
the wild man of Borneo.

317
00:23:47.117 --> 00:23:50.724
- Here you go.
- Well, thank you.

318
00:23:50.788 --> 00:23:53.132
Guess who's here?
Who?

319
00:23:53.190 --> 00:23:55.864
Ruth. She's stayin'
with us this summer...

320
00:23:55.926 --> 00:23:59.339
and will be in charge of all the young
people's activities at the church.

321
00:23:59.396 --> 00:24:04.175
- Is that why you wanted to see me?
- We have so many things planned.

322
00:24:04.234 --> 00:24:06.373
Ruth?

323
00:24:06.437 --> 00:24:09.941
- You remember my youngest child?
- Of course I do.

324
00:24:10.007 --> 00:24:11.953
Hi, Idgie.

325
00:24:13.510 --> 00:24:16.013
Hi.

326
00:24:19.583 --> 00:24:22.792
Maybe this isn't
such a good idea.

327
00:24:22.853 --> 00:24:25.424
Oh, it's got to work.

328
00:24:25.489 --> 00:24:28.993
Somebody's got to help her. I can't.

329
00:24:29.693 --> 00:24:33.368
Are you sure you want to go
to this river club, Miss Ruth?

330
00:24:33.430 --> 00:24:35.376
These ain't no
churchgoing folks.

331
00:24:35.432 --> 00:24:38.675
I'll do just fine, George,
thank you.

332
00:24:38.735 --> 00:24:41.181
Oh, excuse me.

333
00:24:41.238 --> 00:24:44.549
Is Idgie Threadgoode here
by any chance?

334
00:24:44.608 --> 00:24:47.418
Come on in, honey.
She's right down here.

335
00:24:47.478 --> 00:24:50.925
- Here? Okay.
- Uh-huh.

336
00:24:50.981 --> 00:24:53.621
I'll see you,
Grady Kilgore,

337
00:24:53.684 --> 00:24:55.755
and I'll
raise you twenty.

338
00:24:55.819 --> 00:24:58.390
You ain't got nothin'!

339
00:24:58.455 --> 00:25:01.766
Maybe I do and
maybe I don't.

340
00:25:01.825 --> 00:25:06.069
Put your money where
your mouth is, Mr. Sheriff.

341
00:25:10.100 --> 00:25:12.740
Well, look what
the cat drug in!

342
00:25:12.803 --> 00:25:16.683
I came to talk to you.

343
00:25:16.740 --> 00:25:19.118
You're gonna have to wait.
I'm busy.

344
00:25:19.176 --> 00:25:21.782
Come on, Grady, this is your
big chance. You in or out?

345
00:25:21.845 --> 00:25:24.291
I'll make you
a rich man.

346
00:25:24.348 --> 00:25:27.352
You just bluffin' again
as usual

347
00:25:27.417 --> 00:25:30.421
I'm afraid you're gonna have to excuse
Idgie. She's goin' home for dinner.

348
00:25:30.487 --> 00:25:32.660
- Say good-bye, Idgie.
- Where you goin'?

349
00:25:32.723 --> 00:25:37.103
- Where the hell you goin' with my money?
- We're goin' home!

350
00:25:37.160 --> 00:25:41.108
- Who are you to boss me around?
- The one holdin' your money!

351
00:25:41.164 --> 00:25:43.110
Give it back.

352
00:25:43.166 --> 00:25:45.305
Now, get in the car.

353
00:25:47.170 --> 00:25:50.413
All right.
I'll get in the car.

354
00:25:50.474 --> 00:25:52.977
You win!

355
00:25:53.043 --> 00:25:56.024
Come on.

356
00:25:56.079 --> 00:25:57.649
Sucker!

357
00:25:57.714 --> 00:25:59.751
I'll leave when I want!

358
00:25:59.816 --> 00:26:03.628
I don't know how you can break
your mother's heart like you do.

359
00:26:03.687 --> 00:26:05.860
I'm not doin' anything
to my mother.

360
00:26:05.923 --> 00:26:08.494
Oh, no? Why do you think
I'm here for the summer?

361
00:26:08.559 --> 00:26:11.938
Your mother was so worried, she thought I
might be able to talk some sense into you.

362
00:26:11.995 --> 00:26:14.339
But you're too busy
being selfish!

363
00:26:14.398 --> 00:26:17.379
What are you
talkin' about?

364
00:26:17.434 --> 00:26:21.143
You're not the only one
who lost Buddy.

365
00:26:21.204 --> 00:26:23.309
We all miss him...

366
00:26:23.373 --> 00:26:26.252
but turning your back on
your family is not gonna help.

367
00:26:28.612 --> 00:26:30.683
What's he got to do
with anything?

368
00:26:30.747 --> 00:26:34.889
I oaks like you 're the one with
the problem forgetting my brother.

369
00:26:39.256 --> 00:26:41.759
Why just ten miles a way..

370
00:26:41.825 --> 00:26:43.736
Down by the river,

371
00:26:43.794 --> 00:26:46.035
there lurks
a den of the devil...

372
00:26:46.096 --> 00:26:49.942
Where liquor
and gamblin'...

373
00:26:50.000 --> 00:26:52.844
and sin abide!

374
00:26:52.903 --> 00:26:56.578
Snakes and serpents-

375
00:26:56.640 --> 00:26:58.813
Hey, Scroggins!

376
00:26:58.875 --> 00:27:02.846
You're finally preachin' about
somethin' you're kin to... snakes!

377
00:27:02.913 --> 00:27:06.224
As I said,

378
00:27:06.283 --> 00:27:11.426
snakes and serpents
take many disguises.

379
00:27:11.488 --> 00:27:14.765
Let's turn to page 53
in our hymnal.

380
00:27:20.864 --> 00:27:23.868
Yoo-hoo!

381
00:27:23.934 --> 00:27:28.747
Big George thought
I might find you here.

382
00:27:31.608 --> 00:27:36.455
If you give me a chance,
a chance to get to know you,

383
00:27:36.513 --> 00:27:40.256
maybe it'll be fun!

384
00:27:40.317 --> 00:27:43.730
Fun?

385
00:27:43.787 --> 00:27:47.064
Idgie,just spend
some time with me.

386
00:27:47.124 --> 00:27:49.070
Please?

387
00:27:49.126 --> 00:27:51.072
Suit yourself.

388
00:27:51.762 --> 00:27:54.436
You sure you don't
wanna back out?

389
00:27:54.498 --> 00:27:57.707
- It's not too late.
- I'm sure.

390
00:27:57.768 --> 00:28:00.112
Here, hold this.

391
00:28:02.105 --> 00:28:04.813
Tell me now,
you like trains?

392
00:28:04.875 --> 00:28:08.687
- Yes.
- Good.

393
00:28:08.745 --> 00:28:12.659
We'll get along
just fine!

394
00:28:14.151 --> 00:28:17.655
Boy, did we
luck out tonight.

395
00:28:20.524 --> 00:28:22.765
Hop in.

396
00:28:22.826 --> 00:28:25.363
Hop?

397
00:28:25.429 --> 00:28:28.467
Oh. Give me
your hand.

398
00:28:28.532 --> 00:28:31.012
Put your foot
up there.

399
00:28:40.310 --> 00:28:42.449
Hold that.

400
00:28:43.346 --> 00:28:46.156
Ooo-ooo!
Look at all this!

401
00:28:50.754 --> 00:28:54.327
Don't you think we should get off
the train? It's startin' to move.

402
00:28:54.391 --> 00:28:58.203
No. The fun
just started!

403
00:29:01.531 --> 00:29:03.943
You all right?

404
00:29:04.000 --> 00:29:08.244
Well, sometimes I get
a little dizzy lookin' down.

405
00:29:08.305 --> 00:29:11.013
Don't look down.

406
00:29:23.887 --> 00:29:27.664
- What are you doin'?
- Come on. Look.

407
00:29:27.724 --> 00:29:30.637
They're throwin'
away food!

408
00:29:34.464 --> 00:29:37.104
You talk about
"give unto others."

409
00:29:37.167 --> 00:29:40.239
Yes, but this food
isn't yours to give.

410
00:29:40.303 --> 00:29:42.476
That's church talk.

411
00:29:42.539 --> 00:29:45.543
I've seen those same people
over at church on Sunday...

412
00:29:45.609 --> 00:29:48.249
over at the river club every
other night of the week,

413
00:29:48.311 --> 00:29:52.191
doin' anything
but pray. Come on.

414
00:30:08.098 --> 00:30:09.736
- More!
- Give me some.

415
00:30:35.058 --> 00:30:38.437
Okay, time to get off.

416
00:30:39.062 --> 00:30:41.042
We gotta jump.

417
00:30:41.097 --> 00:30:43.703
Lump?

418
00:30:43.767 --> 00:30:46.839
Yeah jump. The next stop's
five miles down the tracks.

419
00:30:46.903 --> 00:30:48.905
I don't wanna walk
that far back.

420
00:30:48.972 --> 00:30:51.851
Are you crazy?

421
00:30:51.908 --> 00:30:54.286
You're not kiddin'.

422
00:30:54.344 --> 00:30:58.019
Well...

423
00:30:58.081 --> 00:31:00.561
I give up. Jump. -

424
00:31:00.617 --> 00:31:03.894
I'll tell Mama I'm not
a good influence on you-

425
00:31:03.954 --> 00:31:06.230
You'll never jump,
will you?

426
00:31:08.258 --> 00:31:11.398
Don't say "never"
to me.

427
00:31:23.440 --> 00:31:26.216
Towanda!

428
00:31:39.089 --> 00:31:41.695
- You all right?
- I'm fine.

429
00:31:41.758 --> 00:31:45.331
I'm all right.

430
00:31:45.395 --> 00:31:47.534
Ow!

431
00:31:47.597 --> 00:31:49.941
Does this hurt?

432
00:31:50.000 --> 00:31:52.776
Guess so.

433
00:31:52.836 --> 00:31:55.146
- We better get you to
a doc-doctor. - Shit!

434
00:31:55.205 --> 00:31:57.310
Which way is it?

435
00:31:57.374 --> 00:32:00.981
About two miles
down the tracks.

436
00:32:01.044 --> 00:32:03.285
All right.
let's go.

437
00:32:05.081 --> 00:32:08.585
You'll never be able
to carry me that far.

438
00:32:08.652 --> 00:32:11.360
I know.
Never say never.

439
00:32:11.421 --> 00:32:15.563
I'm not carryin' you.
You're walkin'.

440
00:32:21.498 --> 00:32:26.243
Thank you, Julian.
I owe you one.

441
00:32:38.148 --> 00:32:40.094
Uh. Ow.

442
00:32:40.150 --> 00:32:43.723
Aren't you ready yet?

443
00:32:43.787 --> 00:32:45.892
What?

444
00:32:47.958 --> 00:32:51.030
This doesn't have anything
to do with trains, does it?

445
00:32:51.928 --> 00:32:54.169
You like honey?

446
00:32:54.230 --> 00:32:56.210
Yeah, I like honey.

447
00:32:56.266 --> 00:32:58.268
- Fresh honey?
- Yeah.

448
00:32:58.335 --> 00:33:01.873
Me too.
There it is.

449
00:33:01.938 --> 00:33:06.148
There what... is?

450
00:33:06.209 --> 00:33:10.089
You'll see soon enough.

451
00:33:14.050 --> 00:33:16.291
Now... stay here.

452
00:33:16.353 --> 00:33:19.300
No matter what happens,
don't move.

453
00:33:19.356 --> 00:33:22.633
What are you
gonna do?

454
00:33:57.627 --> 00:33:59.732
Ah.

455
00:34:34.330 --> 00:34:37.937
Here you are, madam.
This is for you.

456
00:34:38.001 --> 00:34:42.381
Why did you do that?
You could have been killed.

457
00:34:42.439 --> 00:34:45.943
I'm sorry.

458
00:34:46.009 --> 00:34:48.717
Don't you want
the honey?

459
00:34:48.778 --> 00:34:52.123
I got it
just for you.

460
00:34:52.182 --> 00:34:54.662
It's all right.
I do it all the time.

461
00:34:54.717 --> 00:34:58.494
I never get stung,
honest.

462
00:34:58.555 --> 00:35:00.557
Don't be
mad at me, Ruth.

463
00:35:00.623 --> 00:35:04.537
Idgie.
I'm not mad at you.

464
00:35:04.594 --> 00:35:07.165
No foolin'?

465
00:35:13.970 --> 00:35:16.678
Is it bad,
what I did?

466
00:35:16.739 --> 00:35:19.083
No.

467
00:35:19.142 --> 00:35:21.315
I thought I might
be crazy or somethin'.

468
00:35:21.377 --> 00:35:24.187
No, no.

469
00:35:24.247 --> 00:35:27.922
I've heard there were people
who could charm bees.

470
00:35:27.984 --> 00:35:31.625
I've just never seen
it done... before today.

471
00:35:33.523 --> 00:35:37.903
You're just a bee charmer,
Idgie Threadgoode.

472
00:35:37.961 --> 00:35:42.432
That's what you are,
a bee charmer.

473
00:35:42.499 --> 00:35:45.241
Here, you want
to taste it?

474
00:35:51.374 --> 00:35:54.116
"Satan started to laugh
at job's devotion.

475
00:35:54.177 --> 00:35:59.422
"He bet God that job would
never have so much faith...

476
00:35:59.482 --> 00:36:01.587
"if he didn't have
so many blessings.

477
00:36:01.651 --> 00:36:05.531
"He went on and on so long and
so much that God finally agreed...

478
00:36:05.588 --> 00:36:08.296
"to let Satan
put Job to a test.

479
00:36:08.358 --> 00:36:11.498
"Suddenly from bein'
on top of the world,

480
00:36:11.561 --> 00:36:15.202
Job was plunged down into
the deepest pits of misery."

481
00:36:17.233 --> 00:36:19.975
Surprise!

482
00:36:22.238 --> 00:36:24.184
Idgie Threadgoode!

483
00:36:24.240 --> 00:36:26.186
Tonight we're gonna have
a real party.

484
00:36:26.242 --> 00:36:28.483
Drink this... and then,
we're gonna play some poker.

485
00:36:28.545 --> 00:36:32.425
I don't know how to play
poker and I never drink...

486
00:36:32.482 --> 00:36:34.484
but thank you anyway.

487
00:36:39.622 --> 00:36:42.125
Here comes the windup.

488
00:36:42.192 --> 00:36:44.536
Burn that ball in here.
Burn 'em in here!

489
00:36:44.594 --> 00:36:48.974
- Right in the pocket.
- I don't know how to bat.

490
00:36:49.032 --> 00:36:51.842
And you don't drink,
either.

491
00:36:51.901 --> 00:36:55.007
- It's gonna be a spitter.
- Hold the bat and swing

492
00:36:55.071 --> 00:36:56.812
Spitter?

493
00:36:56.873 --> 00:37:00.082
- She gonna spit at me?
- She's gonna spit on the ball

494
00:37:00.143 --> 00:37:03.352
Swing that bat!
