00:55:42.164 --> 00:55:44.610
With your
pretty complexion...

739
00:55:44.666 --> 00:55:48.443
I'll bet you'll be
great with cosmetics.

740
00:55:49.838 --> 00:55:53.411
I know how
you feel.

741
00:55:53.475 --> 00:55:56.922
I was about your age
when I had my child.

742
00:55:56.978 --> 00:55:59.481
Then I went through
the change of life.

743
00:55:59.548 --> 00:56:04.190
- I didn't know you had a child.
- Yes, I did.

744
00:56:04.252 --> 00:56:07.233
Albert.

745
00:56:07.289 --> 00:56:11.897
When he was born, the doctor said
it would be best if I didn't see him.

746
00:56:11.960 --> 00:56:16.067
He said his mind would never
develop past the age of five,

747
00:56:16.131 --> 00:56:19.112
and I should just put him
in an institution...

748
00:56:19.167 --> 00:56:23.843
because the burden of raisin' a
child like that would be too great.

749
00:56:25.040 --> 00:56:29.887
Well, I thought
about Ruth.

750
00:56:31.446 --> 00:56:33.790
She always said...

751
00:56:33.849 --> 00:56:37.296
there was a separate
God for children.

752
00:56:37.352 --> 00:56:42.267
Sol smiled at him and
I asked for the baby.

753
00:56:42.324 --> 00:56:47.034
Oh, how could anybody think
that sweet, precious baby...

754
00:56:47.095 --> 00:56:49.336
could ever
be a burden?

755
00:56:49.398 --> 00:56:53.710
Why, from the minute he was born,
Albert was the joy of my life,

756
00:56:53.769 --> 00:56:56.807
the Lord's
greatest gift.

757
00:56:56.872 --> 00:57:01.446
I don't believe there was a purer
soul ever lived on this earth.

758
00:57:01.510 --> 00:57:04.491
I had him with me
till he was 30.

759
00:57:04.546 --> 00:57:08.824
Then he went to sleep
and didn't wake up.

760
00:57:10.218 --> 00:57:12.960
Sometimes I can't wait to get
to heaven to see him again.

761
00:57:16.591 --> 00:57:18.537
Whoa!

762
00:57:18.593 --> 00:57:21.870
Shit!
It's a boy!

763
00:57:24.065 --> 00:57:27.774
I think a prayer of
thanksgivin' would be in order.

764
00:57:27.836 --> 00:57:31.841
Goddamn it to hell, son-of-a-bitch,
she did it! Here's to Ruth!

765
00:57:31.907 --> 00:57:36.185
Idgie always did have a way
with words around the reverend.

766
00:57:36.878 --> 00:57:40.382
Well, Ruth had a baby

767
00:57:40.449 --> 00:57:43.191
She named him Buddy-
Buddy junior.

768
00:57:43.251 --> 00:57:48.394
Papa went out and borrowed money so
Ruth and Idgie could start a cafe,

769
00:57:48.457 --> 00:57:50.698
the Whistle Stop 6.22%.

770
00:58:26.928 --> 00:58:29.204
Miss Idgie
can you get the door?

771
00:58:29.264 --> 00:58:32.871
Yes.
Big George.

772
00:58:32.934 --> 00:58:36.245
Miss Ruth, me and the missus
want to thank you...

773
00:58:36.304 --> 00:58:38.477
for sendin' that soup
over last night.

774
00:58:38.540 --> 00:58:42.784
- I'll pay you when I get ahead.
- You don't owe me, Ocie.

775
00:58:42.844 --> 00:58:45.518
- Thank you.
- I'm just glad they're better.

776
00:58:45.580 --> 00:58:49.255
- How is this, by the way?
- It's good, very good.

777
00:58:49.317 --> 00:58:52.787
I'm not happy
till I see clean plates.

778
00:58:55.457 --> 00:58:57.994
Can't go on,
Idgie.

779
00:58:58.059 --> 00:59:00.369
I'm talking to you
as a friend.

780
00:59:00.428 --> 00:59:04.899
- There's people in this town,
paying customers too- - There you go.

781
00:59:04.966 --> 00:59:08.607
But some people
don't like you...

782
00:59:08.670 --> 00:59:10.843
sellin' to coloreds.

783
00:59:10.906 --> 00:59:12.886
Here you go.

784
00:59:12.941 --> 00:59:16.855
Tell you what. Next time
those "some people" come here,

785
00:59:16.912 --> 00:59:19.358
I'm gonna ask if they
don't want anybody to know...

786
00:59:19.414 --> 00:59:21.587
who they are
under those sheets...

787
00:59:21.650 --> 00:59:25.757
when they go marchin'
in those stupid parades,

788
00:59:25.820 --> 00:59:28.664
how come they don't have
sense to change their shoes?

789
00:59:28.755 --> 00:59:32.100
- Hold on there.
- Y'all ain't foolin' anybody.

790
00:59:32.159 --> 00:59:36.369
I'd recognize those size 14
clodhoppers you got anywhere.

791
00:59:36.430 --> 00:59:39.570
- Just a minute, Idgie.
- More pie, Grady?

792
00:59:39.633 --> 00:59:42.136
No, thank you, Ruth.

793
00:59:42.202 --> 00:59:45.775
Idgie, I'll talk
to the boys.

794
00:59:45.839 --> 00:59:48.012
You just keep them
on out back there, ya hear?

795
00:59:48.075 --> 00:59:52.854
- Bye, Ruth.
- Bye, Grady.

796
00:59:53.547 --> 00:59:54.992
You're gonna get yourself
in a heap of trouble.

797
00:59:55.048 --> 00:59:59.053
What, Grady?
He's harmless.

798
00:59:59.119 --> 01:00:03.158
You shoulda seen that
big ox down by the river.

799
01:00:03.223 --> 01:00:07.262
Three solid days, drunk as
a dog, cryin' like a baby...

800
01:00:07.327 --> 01:00:10.103
'cause Joe, that ol' colored
man that raised him, died.

801
01:00:10.163 --> 01:00:12.109
- Remember that, Sipsey?
- Yes'm.

802
01:00:12.165 --> 01:00:14.873
- He sure ain't' jokin' now, is he, son?
- No, ma'am.

803
01:00:14.935 --> 01:00:17.313
He won't even sit in the same
room and have a meal today.

804
01:00:17.371 --> 01:00:22.320
Don't make no sense. Big ox like Grady
won't sit next to a colored child,

805
01:00:22.376 --> 01:00:25.823
but he eats eggs
- Shoot right out of a chicken's ass.

806
01:00:50.737 --> 01:00:53.411
Come on, Smokey,
let's go for a walk.

807
01:01:02.382 --> 01:01:05.158
I'm sorry about
spillin' my food, ma'am.

808
01:01:05.218 --> 01:01:08.893
I'll just
head on.

809
01:01:17.597 --> 01:01:20.635
See that piece
of land over there?

810
01:01:20.701 --> 01:01:23.511
See it?
That used to be a lake.

811
01:01:23.570 --> 01:01:25.572
Yeah.

812
01:01:25.639 --> 01:01:27.585
This one November,

813
01:01:27.641 --> 01:01:29.587
all these ducks
come by...

814
01:01:29.643 --> 01:01:32.920
and they landed
on that lake.

815
01:01:32.979 --> 01:01:37.086
Then the temperature dropped so
fast, the whole lake just froze.

816
01:01:37.150 --> 01:01:40.188
Then the ducks took off
and took the lake with 'em.

817
01:01:40.253 --> 01:01:43.063
Now that lake's somewhere
in Georgia, the way I hear it.

818
01:01:43.123 --> 01:01:45.797
Go on now.

819
01:01:59.406 --> 01:02:01.886
God bless you,
ma'am.

820
01:02:30.871 --> 01:02:33.147
Here, try this.

821
01:02:36.910 --> 01:02:40.949
- So what do you think?
- They're okay.

822
01:02:41.014 --> 01:02:44.723
- The truth.
- Well-

823
01:02:47.320 --> 01:02:50.096
They're terrible.

824
01:02:50.157 --> 01:02:55.106
Oh, well, don't be shy.
Tell me how you feel.

825
01:02:55.162 --> 01:02:57.699
I will.

826
01:03:10.377 --> 01:03:12.550
What'd you go
and do that for?

827
01:03:15.348 --> 01:03:18.625
I just thought you needed
a little coolin' off.

828
01:03:18.685 --> 01:03:22.792
You're right.

829
01:03:36.136 --> 01:03:39.549
Try these.

830
01:03:43.376 --> 01:03:46.050
I think we need
to make a little paste.

831
01:04:05.131 --> 01:04:07.873
What in the name of
Christmas are you two doing?

832
01:04:07.934 --> 01:04:09.880
She's tryin' to teach me how to cook.

833
01:04:09.936 --> 01:04:12.815
Look at those
fried green tomatoes.

834
01:04:16.910 --> 01:04:21.256
You better stop this. I'm gonna have
to arrest you for disorderly conduct.

835
01:04:21.314 --> 01:04:23.794
Arrest us then.
Let me handle this.

836
01:04:23.850 --> 01:04:26.126
- All right.
- Grady.

837
01:04:27.921 --> 01:04:30.424
Ha-ha-ha!

838
01:04:30.490 --> 01:04:34.666
Arrest us.
Go ahead, arrest us.

839
01:04:34.728 --> 01:04:39.108
Ruth, I have to say it. I believe
Idgie's been a bad influence on ya.

840
01:04:39.165 --> 01:04:42.305
I agree.

841
01:05:21.308 --> 01:05:24.414
I'll be back in a minute.

842
01:05:24.477 --> 01:05:26.548
Y'all keep the show
going till then.

843
01:05:26.613 --> 01:05:28.650
We ain't goin'
nowhere.

844
01:05:29.783 --> 01:05:32.923
- ... down again.
- She's still poorly.

845
01:05:32.986 --> 01:05:35.990
Where's the baby?
Who are you?

846
01:05:38.358 --> 01:05:40.736
What do you want?

847
01:05:40.794 --> 01:05:43.638
Frank!

848
01:05:45.332 --> 01:05:47.938
Get outta here.

849
01:05:48.001 --> 01:05:51.744
- Get on outta here!
- Go on, get outta here and leave us alone.

850
01:05:51.805 --> 01:05:54.115
Come on now, Ruth.

851
01:05:54.174 --> 01:05:58.884
You wouldn't deny a father the
right to see his son, would ya?

852
01:05:58.945 --> 01:06:01.755
You git, I say.
Scat you!

853
01:06:01.815 --> 01:06:05.695
Damn! Gimme that. Let it go!

854
01:06:12.459 --> 01:06:17.568
Well, that's my boy,
isn't it?

855
01:06:22.369 --> 01:06:24.975
Everything all right, ma'am?

856
01:06:26.740 --> 01:06:30.745
Our guest
is just leavin'.

857
01:06:30.810 --> 01:06:32.756
Come on, Frank,
let's go.

858
01:06:36.216 --> 01:06:39.163
I'll be back.

859
01:06:39.219 --> 01:06:42.996
In the end, you and
the baby gonna be back.

860
01:06:46.159 --> 01:06:50.198
I ain't scared
of you! No, sir!

861
01:06:50.263 --> 01:06:53.676
You should be.

862
01:07:03.410 --> 01:07:05.788
Mind your manners, boy!

863
01:07:14.687 --> 01:07:17.065
Grady,

864
01:07:17.123 --> 01:07:20.366
what does Gladys think
of you stayin' out late...

865
01:07:20.427 --> 01:07:24.739
and losin' your money to me
in poker night after night?

866
01:07:25.565 --> 01:07:28.409
She likes it
just fine.

867
01:07:32.972 --> 01:07:35.612
- They got Big George.
- Idgie!

868
01:07:35.675 --> 01:07:38.178
- Let go of him!
- Let me handle this!

869
01:07:38.244 --> 01:07:42.124
We seen how you treat your niggers
around here and we don't like it.

870
01:07:42.182 --> 01:07:46.460
I'm the law in these parts. I don't
care what you like or don't like.

871
01:07:46.519 --> 01:07:48.499
Turn him loose.

872
01:07:48.555 --> 01:07:51.764
Don't get riled up,
nigger lover.

873
01:07:51.825 --> 01:07:56.296
You deaf or somethin'?
I said, let him go!

874
01:07:56.362 --> 01:07:59.343
- Before you get yourselves in a whole lot of trouble!
- Calm down.

875
01:07:59.399 --> 01:08:02.175
We wanted to have
a little get-together...

876
01:08:02.235 --> 01:08:05.216
and make sure we see
eye to eye on some things.

877
01:08:05.271 --> 01:08:08.718
You hear me now?

878
01:08:08.775 --> 01:08:10.812
Let's let him go, boys.

879
01:08:10.877 --> 01:08:12.584
We've had enough fun
for one night.

880
01:08:12.645 --> 01:08:14.591
- Turn him loose.
- Come on.

881
01:08:14.647 --> 01:08:16.627
No, you're gonna
get in trouble.

882
01:08:19.185 --> 01:08:21.722
Well, now,
that's more like it.

883
01:08:21.788 --> 01:08:24.735
Seems I don't recognize
any of you boys.

884
01:08:24.791 --> 01:08:27.032
Y'all ain't from Whistle Stop,
are you?

885
01:08:30.063 --> 01:08:32.134
This ought to do it.

886
01:08:32.198 --> 01:08:35.202
I want to thank you,
Miss Idgie.

887
01:08:35.268 --> 01:08:40.445
Forget it. You'd have
done the same for me.

888
01:08:40.507 --> 01:08:44.319
Try to get some sleep.

889
01:08:49.115 --> 01:08:52.221
Who the hell
were those assholes?

890
01:08:52.285 --> 01:08:57.564
They's just some old boys from Georgia
come over here to put a scare in you.

891
01:08:57.624 --> 01:09:00.070
Well, it worked.

892
01:09:00.126 --> 01:09:02.834
One of 'em was here
the other day for something,

893
01:09:02.896 --> 01:09:05.433
seen you sellin' food
to coloreds.

894
01:09:05.498 --> 01:09:09.571
They decided to come back,
shake you up a bit.

895
01:09:09.636 --> 01:09:13.083
I told 'em we don't need anybody
from Georgia comin' over here...

896
01:09:13.139 --> 01:09:15.676
tellin' us what
we can or cannot do.

897
01:09:15.742 --> 01:09:20.919
They won't be back. I
guaran-gol-damn-tee you that.

898
01:09:20.980 --> 01:09:24.052
One other thing,
little Miss Smarty-pants,

899
01:09:24.117 --> 01:09:28.395
I do not wear a size 14 shoe...

900
01:09:28.454 --> 01:09:32.027
and I don't
much care for parades,

901
01:09:32.091 --> 01:09:35.698
bedsheets or otherwise.

902
01:09:47.040 --> 01:09:52.649
Hey. What's the matter?

903
01:09:52.712 --> 01:09:56.125
It was Frank.
He saw the baby.

904
01:09:56.182 --> 01:09:59.288
- You sure it was him?
- Yes, I'm sure.

905
01:09:59.352 --> 01:10:02.265
So that's why those
Kluxers were here.

906
01:10:02.322 --> 01:10:05.667
Let me take him.

907
01:10:07.093 --> 01:10:11.303
Don't worry. I mean, if he's
dumb enough to come back here,

908
01:10:11.364 --> 01:10:14.277
Grady and the Alabama boys
will take care of him.

909
01:10:14.334 --> 01:10:18.373
If they don't,
I'll think of somethin'.

910
01:10:18.438 --> 01:10:21.351
Don't take
any chances.

911
01:10:21.407 --> 01:10:24.718
Promise me you won't do
anythin' crazy, no matter what.

912
01:10:24.777 --> 01:10:28.350
Me?
Not me.

913
01:10:30.416 --> 01:10:33.795
I'm gonna
put him down.

914
01:10:33.853 --> 01:10:35.730
Hey little Buddy

915
01:10:35.922 --> 01:10:39.165
That was the last
anyone saw of Frank Bennett...

916
01:10:39.225 --> 01:10:41.535
until the night
of the town follies.

917
01:10:41.594 --> 01:10:46.009
Ruth was away at one of the
Reverend Scroggins' many revivals.

918
01:10:46.065 --> 01:10:49.012
One thing a woman expects
when she gets married...

919
01:10:49.068 --> 01:10:51.014
is sympathy.

920
01:10:51.070 --> 01:10:53.482
Haven't you got that
since you married me?

921
01:10:53.539 --> 01:10:58.010
I sure have...
from the whole town.

922
01:11:29.042 --> 01:11:32.387
- Hey there!
- You got to come quick.

923
01:11:32.445 --> 01:11:35.619
Well, the show
has hardly begun.

924
01:11:35.682 --> 01:11:38.424
You got to come quick now.
You hear me?

925
01:11:41.154 --> 01:11:43.464
- Run, get help! Run, quick!
- Where's the baby?

926
01:11:43.523 --> 01:11:45.560
Never mind.

927
01:12:04.977 --> 01:12:10.518
Excuse me, sir. I don't believe
you should be goin' anywhere...

928
01:12:10.583 --> 01:12:13.154
with Ruth's baby.

929
01:12:57.897 --> 01:12:59.877
Thank you.

930
01:12:59.932 --> 01:13:02.378
Hi there. What can I do for you boys?

931
01:13:02.435 --> 01:13:04.381
- Idgie.
- Grady.

932
01:13:04.437 --> 01:13:07.611
- This here is Sheriff Curtis Smoote.
- Hi there.

933
01:13:07.673 --> 01:13:10.745
- He's over here from Georgia. He's lookin' for a fella.
- Oh.

934
01:13:13.913 --> 01:13:15.950
- You recognize him?
- No.

935
01:13:16.015 --> 01:13:20.794
That's my husband, but I
haven't seen him in months.

936
01:13:20.853 --> 01:13:24.096
I heard he got run over
by a Brinks armored truck.

937
01:13:24.157 --> 01:13:26.194
What's he done?

938
01:13:26.259 --> 01:13:30.264
Nothin' that we know of. We're tryin'
to find out what's been did to him.

939
01:13:30.329 --> 01:13:33.833
He told his hired man he was
comin' to see his wife and baby,

940
01:13:33.900 --> 01:13:37.905
but he ain't never
showed up back home.

941
01:13:37.970 --> 01:13:40.678
Hell, I told him
if he showed up in this town,

942
01:13:40.740 --> 01:13:42.879
we'd all have known.

943
01:13:42.942 --> 01:13:45.388
Looks a little sissified
to me.

944
01:13:45.445 --> 01:13:49.450
From what I hear,
most you boys in Georgia...

945
01:13:49.515 --> 01:13:50.960
are a little light
on your feet

946
01:13:51.017 --> 01:13:54.191
That's the way
I heard it.

947
01:13:54.253 --> 01:13:56.392
Could I interest you
in some pie?

948
01:13:56.456 --> 01:14:00.370
No, ma'am, but that
barbecue sure smells good.

949
01:14:00.426 --> 01:14:03.873
Best damn barbecue
in the state of Alabama.

950
01:14:33.092 --> 01:14:35.732
Here you go.
That's your 4th one today.

951
01:14:35.795 --> 01:14:38.639
I swear you're about
to eat up all my barbecue.

952
01:14:38.698 --> 01:14:44.515
Sit down.

953
01:14:46.105 --> 01:14:48.312
You ain't foolin' me,
girlie girl.

954
01:14:48.374 --> 01:14:51.048
I know who you are.

955
01:14:51.110 --> 01:14:54.284
I heard from Bennett's hired hand
that you threatened to kill Frank.

956
01:14:54.347 --> 01:14:57.556
He ain't showed up
dead yet.

957
01:14:57.617 --> 01:15:01.394
But if he does, you in a whole
mess of trouble. You understand?

958
01:15:01.454 --> 01:15:05.527
What we talkin' about
is murder here.

959
01:15:05.591 --> 01:15:08.800
Runnin' afoul of the law
and nobody gets away with that,

960
01:15:08.861 --> 01:15:12.673
not even a bunch
of Alabama smart alecks.

961
01:15:12.732 --> 01:15:15.372
If I find so much
as a hair of his head,

962
01:15:15.434 --> 01:15:18.108
I'll arrest you faster
than you can slap a tick,

963
01:15:18.170 --> 01:15:23.745
'cause I'm the law,
and you cant beat the law

964
01:15:43.996 --> 01:15:47.375
Hey there.

965
01:15:47.433 --> 01:15:50.039
Tell me what he said.

966
01:15:50.102 --> 01:15:54.983
Smoote's? I told you.
He said...

967
01:15:55.041 --> 01:15:58.352
that was the best damn
barbecue he ever had.

968
01:15:58.411 --> 01:16:01.153
- That's all?
- No.

969
01:16:01.213 --> 01:16:07.630
- What else?
- He said the pie was pretty good too.

970
01:16:12.558 --> 01:16:15.232
You sure you ain't
never seen this man, boy?

971
01:16:15.294 --> 01:16:18.935
Yes, sir, and I already told ya,
I ain't never seen him.

972
01:16:18.998 --> 01:16:21.501
You'd do anything for
Miss Idgie, wouldn't ya, boy?

973
01:16:23.402 --> 01:16:25.348
Yes, sir.

974
01:16:28.574 --> 01:16:32.181
Would ya kill for her?
Did ya kill for her?

975
01:16:39.552 --> 01:16:41.691
No, sir.

976
01:16:41.754 --> 01:16:46.601
Well, now, maybe one of these
days you'll tell the truth.

977
01:16:48.628 --> 01:16:51.336
Just remember, we hang
lyin' niggers in Georgia...

978
01:16:51.397 --> 01:16:54.378
just as fast as
they do in Alabama.

979
01:16:54.433 --> 01:16:58.210
Yes, sir, I remember.

980
01:17:35.775 --> 01:17:40.224
Sorry.

981
01:17:40.279 --> 01:17:45.228
- What are ya doin' in here?
- No milk in the house.

982
01:17:45.284 --> 01:17:47.389
Where were you?

983
01:17:47.453 --> 01:17:50.400
Takin' care of business,
havin' a good time.

984
01:17:53.125 --> 01:17:56.698
I've been thinkin'
maybe I should move on...

985
01:17:56.762 --> 01:17:59.242
because of Frank
and all.

986
01:17:59.298 --> 01:18:04.247
I just don't want
you to feel like...

987
01:18:04.303 --> 01:18:07.250
you have
to look out for us.

988
01:18:07.306 --> 01:18:09.752
I just...

989
01:18:09.809 --> 01:18:12.050
don't want to be selfish,
that's all.

990
01:18:12.111 --> 01:18:14.455
Maybe if I wasn't here,
you'd settle down.

991
01:18:14.513 --> 01:18:19.428
I'm as settled
as I ever hope to be.

992
01:18:34.033 --> 01:18:38.743
Then... why can't you
tell me where you were?

993
01:18:48.848 --> 01:18:52.352
I had a dream...
the other night.

994
01:18:52.418 --> 01:18:57.731
I dreamt that
Buddy was gone.

995
01:18:57.790 --> 01:19:02.261
I ran to his crib and there
he was, sleepin' like an angel.

996
01:19:02.328 --> 01:19:04.968
You know,
I thanked God...

997
01:19:05.030 --> 01:19:08.011
for lettin' me
still have Buddy.

998
01:19:08.067 --> 01:19:10.638
And I remembered...

999
01:19:10.703 --> 01:19:14.446
havin' the same reaction
after Frank would beat me,

1000
01:19:14.507 --> 01:19:18.216
thankin' the Lord for givin' me
the strength to take it.

1001
01:19:18.277 --> 01:19:20.450
And I remembered...

1002
01:19:20.513 --> 01:19:24.962
thankin' the Lord
for each day my mother lived,

1003
01:19:26.018 --> 01:19:29.329
even when she was
spittin' up blood...

1004
01:19:29.388 --> 01:19:33.268
and prayin' for me
to kill her.

1005
01:19:33.325 --> 01:19:37.432
I looked in my mother's eyes
pleadin' for me to help her...

1006
01:19:37.496 --> 01:19:42.002
and all I could do
was pray.

1007
01:19:45.771 --> 01:19:49.776
While you were gone,
as I was holdin' Buddy,

1008
01:19:49.842 --> 01:19:54.313
I thought if that bastard,
Frank Bennett...

1009
01:19:54.380 --> 01:19:59.090
ever tries
to take my child,

1010
01:19:59.151 --> 01:20:02.598
I won't pray.

1011
01:20:02.655 --> 01:20:05.261
I'll break his neck.

1012
01:20:08.594 --> 01:20:12.633
Ruth, you don't have to worry
about Frank Bennett anymore.

1013
01:20:12.698 --> 01:20:16.339
How can you say that?
It's his child too.

1014
01:20:16.402 --> 01:20:19.144
He won't give up
on his blood.

1015
01:20:19.205 --> 01:20:22.584
I'm only gonna
tell you this one time.

1016
01:20:24.476 --> 01:20:27.923
Frank Bennett won't
be bothering you no more.

1017
01:20:27.980 --> 01:20:30.756
Understand?

1018
01:20:32.785 --> 01:20:35.197
You killed him,

1019
01:20:35.254 --> 01:20:38.133
didn't you?

1020
01:20:38.190 --> 01:20:40.466
No!

1021
01:20:47.366 --> 01:20:49.312
You don't believe me.

1022
01:20:49.368 --> 01:20:53.942
Right now, I don't know
what to believe.

1023
01:20:56.408 --> 01:20:59.719
Believe me when I tell ya
I don't want ya to move out.

1024
01:21:25.304 --> 01:21:28.649
Finally.

1025
01:21:28.707 --> 01:21:32.450
Thanks, I've been
out here all day.

1026
01:21:59.605 --> 01:22:02.017
Excuse me.
I was waiting for that space.

1027
01:22:02.074 --> 01:22:07.023
- Yeah? Tough!
- Face it, lady, we're younger and faster.

1028
01:22:27.566 --> 01:22:30.479
Towanda.

1029
01:22:33.973 --> 01:22:37.011
Ha-ha-ha-ha!

1030
01:22:37.076 --> 01:22:41.991
Yeah!
Whooo!

1031
01:22:46.352 --> 01:22:48.832
Towanda!

1032
01:22:53.692 --> 01:22:56.502
Yes, ma'am.

1033
01:22:56.562 --> 01:22:59.270
Whoooo!

1034
01:23:02.267 --> 01:23:05.771
- Help, someone!
- What are you doing? Are you crazy?

1035
01:23:05.838 --> 01:23:10.787
Face it, girls. I'm older,
and I have more insurance.

1036
01:23:19.385 --> 01:23:23.026
I never get mad, Mrs.
Threadgoode. Never!

1037
01:23:23.088 --> 01:23:25.659
The way I was raised
it was bad manners.

1038
01:23:25.724 --> 01:23:28.898
Well, I got mad
and it felt terrific.

1039
01:23:28.961 --> 01:23:32.272
I felt like I could beat
the shit outta all those punks!

1040
01:23:32.331 --> 01:23:35.073
Excuse my language.
just beat 'em to a pulp!

1041
01:23:35.134 --> 01:23:37.273
Beat 'em till
they begged for mercy.

1042
01:23:37.336 --> 01:23:39.373
Towanda, the avenger!

1043
01:23:39.438 --> 01:23:42.476
After I wipe out
all the punks of this world,

1044
01:23:42.541 --> 01:23:45.021
I'll take on the wife beaters,
like Frank Bennett,

1045
01:23:45.077 --> 01:23:48.650
and machine gun
their genitals.

1046
01:23:48.714 --> 01:23:50.990
Towanda
will go on the rampage.

1047
01:23:51.050 --> 01:23:53.758
I'll put tiny bombs
in Penthouse and Playboy...

1048
01:23:53.819 --> 01:23:56.026
so they'll explode
when you open 'em.

1049
01:23:56.088 --> 01:24:00.559
I'll ban all fashion models
who weigh less than 130 pounds.

1050
01:24:02.361 --> 01:24:05.934
I'll give half the military
budget to people over 65...

1051
01:24:05.998 --> 01:24:08.740
and declare wrinkles
sexually desirable.

1052
01:24:08.801 --> 01:24:13.443
Towanda, righter of wrongs,
queen beyond compare!

1053
01:24:13.505 --> 01:24:16.816
How many of them
hormones you takin', honey?

1054
01:24:32.291 --> 01:24:34.794
what I can't
understand is...

1055
01:24:34.860 --> 01:24:38.467
how in the hell
you can hit someone...

1056
01:24:38.530 --> 01:24:40.771
six times
by accident.

1057
01:24:40.833 --> 01:24:43.871
Oh, Ed, don't make
such a big deal about it.

1058
01:24:50.275 --> 01:24:54.815
- What the hell is this?
- A low cholesterol meal.

1059
01:24:54.880 --> 01:24:56.826
Happy Valentine's.

1060
01:25:00.085 --> 01:25:03.032
My God!
Are you tryin' to kill me?

1061
01:25:03.088 --> 01:25:06.365
If I was gonna kill ya,
I'd use my hands.

1062
01:25:23.275 --> 01:25:25.881
I'm worried about
my little friend Evelyn.

1063
01:25:25.944 --> 01:25:28.515
She said her husband...

1064
01:25:28.580 --> 01:25:30.890
will just be watching
his sports on TV...

1065
01:25:30.949 --> 01:25:34.123
and she has an urge to hit him
in the head with a baseball bat.

1066
01:25:34.186 --> 01:25:37.065
Hell, that
seems normal to me.

1067
01:25:37.122 --> 01:25:39.124
- Hi Janeen.
- Mm-hmm

1068
01:25:39.191 --> 01:25:41.671
Mrs. Threadgoode, would
you like some crudites?

1069
01:25:41.727 --> 01:25:46.142
Thank you, but this raw stuff
don't sit good with me.

1070
01:25:46.198 --> 01:25:50.374
Mrs. Threadgoode, you
have to tell me something.

1071
01:25:50.435 --> 01:25:55.214
- Did Idgie murder Frank Bennett or not?
- Hold your horses, honey.

1072
01:25:55.274 --> 01:25:58.312
Where were we?

1073
01:25:58.377 --> 01:26:01.119
You didn't kill Ed,
did ya?

1074
01:26:01.180 --> 01:26:04.855
- Not yet.
- Oh, good.

1075
01:26:04.917 --> 01:26:09.593
Anyway, five years had passed
since Frank Bennett disappeared.

1076
01:26:09.655 --> 01:26:14.365
And Smokey Lonesome been missin'
ever since that same terrible night.

1077
01:26:14.426 --> 01:26:17.498
I member the day
when he showed up again.

1078
01:26:18.430 --> 01:26:20.410
My God, son.

1079
01:26:20.465 --> 01:26:22.638
You're the spittin'
image of Ruth.

1080
01:26:22.701 --> 01:26:26.046
Buddy Threadgood,Jr.
Nice to meet you, sir.

1081
01:26:26.104 --> 01:26:28.482
Well, sir,
Smokey Lonesome.

1082
01:26:28.540 --> 01:26:31.749
Curtis Smoote was making one of
his visits to Whistle Stop, Alabama,

1083
01:26:31.810 --> 01:26:34.620
still huntin' and peckin'
for any scrap of evidence...

1084
01:26:34.680 --> 01:26:37.718
about Frank Bennett's
whereabouts.

1085
01:26:37.783 --> 01:26:40.286
Who wants to begin?
Oh, I do.

1086
01:26:40.352 --> 01:26:42.195
- I do, Miss Ruth.
- Thank you.

1087
01:26:42.254 --> 01:26:45.531
We'll begin
on page five.

1088
01:26:45.591 --> 01:26:48.868
Life has a funny way
of working things out.

1089
01:26:48.927 --> 01:26:50.770
Well, hey there!

1090
01:26:50.829 --> 01:26:54.402
- Smokey!
- Idgie?

1091
01:26:54.466 --> 01:26:58.004
Smokey Lonesome!
If it isn't old home week.

1092
01:26:58.070 --> 01:27:01.677
- How are you?
- Well, I'm rattlin' but I'm rollin'.

1093
01:27:01.740 --> 01:27:05.313
- What brings you to these parts?
- Smell of good cookin'.

1094
01:27:05.377 --> 01:27:06.981
Hey, Smokey.

1095
01:27:07.045 --> 01:27:10.117
- Sipsey.
- Let me fix you some lunch.

1096
01:27:10.182 --> 01:27:14.597
You know just about everybody
except Curtis Smoote.

1097
01:27:14.653 --> 01:27:18.157
He's the officer from
over at Valdosta, Georgia.

1098
01:27:18.223 --> 01:27:22.330
He's been lookin' for the same man for
almost 5 years. Very stubborn fella.

1099
01:27:22.394 --> 01:27:26.342
He loves our barbecue.

1100
01:27:26.398 --> 01:27:27.741
Mommy! Mommy!

1101
01:27:35.907 --> 01:27:37.853
Buddy.

1102
01:27:37.909 --> 01:27:39.855
Everybody
outta the way.

1103
01:27:39.911 --> 01:27:43.688
Give him here.
Let him go. I've got him.

1104
01:27:45.651 --> 01:27:47.858
Come on. You're
gonna be all right.

1105
01:27:47.919 --> 01:27:50.263
Open the door!

1106
01:27:50.322 --> 01:27:54.395
Put him in the car.
It's all right, honey

1107
01:28:15.614 --> 01:28:17.525
I can understand...

1108
01:28:17.582 --> 01:28:20.119
having a funeral
for an arm.

1109
01:28:20.185 --> 01:28:23.723
I just don't know why she
insists on callin' him "Stump."?

1110
01:28:23.789 --> 01:28:26.793
She say everybody else gonna
be callin' him that...

1111
01:28:26.858 --> 01:28:30.965
so we might just as well
be the first.

1112
01:28:31.029 --> 01:28:35.205
Okay, ice cream
and cake for everybody.

1113
01:28:35.267 --> 01:28:37.076
Go on.

1114
01:28:41.340 --> 01:28:45.345
My daddy always used to say there
was a separate God for children.

1115
01:28:49.214 --> 01:28:52.752
The good Lord was watchin'
over stump that day.

1116
01:28:52.818 --> 01:28:56.197
But then it started to rain
that month.

1117
01:28:56.254 --> 01:29:01.101
It rained and rained and it
flooded parts of Whistle Stop.

1118
01:29:01.159 --> 01:29:06.302
That's why Grady's deputies stumbled
on to Frank Bennett's pickup truck,

1119
01:29:06.365 --> 01:29:10.370
and I just knew Idgie'd
never get out of this mess.

1120
01:29:10.435 --> 01:29:14.212
Now, you in or out? Remember,
I didn't take any cards.

1121
01:29:14.272 --> 01:29:16.718
Look at me and
let me see your face.

1122
01:29:16.775 --> 01:29:19.016
Idgie, I have to talk
to you. You're bluffin'.

1123
01:29:19.077 --> 01:29:22.854
Why don't you sit in? I'll deal
you a new hand. Gladys won't mind.

1124
01:29:22.914 --> 01:29:25.019
In private, Idgie.

1125
01:29:25.083 --> 01:29:28.121
Excuse us, Ruth.

1126
01:29:28.186 --> 01:29:32.464
- A-ha. - I'm just tryin' to teach
you not to fall for any tricks.

1127
01:29:32.524 --> 01:29:35.164
You're doin'
a great job.

1128
01:29:43.969 --> 01:29:46.210
What's your hurry?

1129
01:29:46.271 --> 01:29:49.514
And what is
so important?

1130
01:29:49.574 --> 01:29:51.815
What's that?

1131
01:29:51.877 --> 01:29:55.222
Somebody found Frank Bennett's
truck in the river.

1132
01:29:55.280 --> 01:29:58.454
What's that got
to do with me?

1133
01:29:58.517 --> 01:30:02.488
Officially, you and Big George
are under arrest for murder.

1134
01:30:02.554 --> 01:30:05.467
You're in my custody
until tomorrow.

1135
01:30:05.524 --> 01:30:08.232
I'm supposed to take you to
Georgia first thing in the morning.

1136
01:30:10.295 --> 01:30:12.502
Unless, of course-

1137
01:30:12.564 --> 01:30:15.306
Well, some people have
been known to pack up...

1138
01:30:15.367 --> 01:30:19.782
and sneak out of town
in the middle of the night.

1139
01:30:21.506 --> 01:30:24.077
What about Big George?

1140
01:30:24.142 --> 01:30:26.884
Well, the way
I figure it,

1141
01:30:26.945 --> 01:30:30.188
they'd be satisfied
if they had him.

1142
01:30:30.248 --> 01:30:32.319
Idgie.
this is serious.

1143
01:30:32.384 --> 01:30:34.990
We're talkin'
murder of a white man.

1144
01:30:35.053 --> 01:30:37.294
Someone's
gonna have to pay.

1145
01:30:37.355 --> 01:30:40.199
Nobody wants
to hang a woman.

1146
01:30:41.726 --> 01:30:43.728
No deal.

1147
01:30:43.795 --> 01:30:46.401
Idgie, I know how you feel
about Big George.

1148
01:30:46.465 --> 01:30:48.604
Hell, we all do.

1149
01:30:48.667 --> 01:30:51.841
But these just
the facts of life.

1150
01:30:54.272 --> 01:30:56.548
I can't do that.

1151
01:30:56.608 --> 01:30:59.384
Take me to jail
if you have to.

1152
01:30:59.444 --> 01:31:01.947
Well, that's what
I thought you'd say...

1153
01:31:02.013 --> 01:31:04.425
'cause you're absolutely,
unconditionally,

1154
01:31:04.483 --> 01:31:08.989
positively the most stubborn
person I've known in my life.

1155
01:31:10.822 --> 01:31:15.532
Idgie and Big George went to
the county jail in Valdosta...

1156
01:31:15.594 --> 01:31:19.406
to await trial for
the murder of Frank Bennett.

1157
01:31:19.464 --> 01:31:21.603
They didn't have
to wait too long.

1158
01:31:21.666 --> 01:31:25.079
- Did you know Frank Bennett?
- No, sir.

1159
01:31:25.136 --> 01:31:27.548
You mean, you
never met the man...

1160
01:31:27.606 --> 01:31:32.146
- whose wife, Ruth, is your business partner?
- That's right.

1161
01:31:32.210 --> 01:31:35.054
You never threatened to kill
Frank Bennett at his home...

1162
01:31:35.113 --> 01:31:38.822
in front of his hired man
in June of 1932?

1163
01:31:38.884 --> 01:31:43.924
- The same Frank Bennett you did not know.
- Oh, that was me, all right.

1164
01:31:43.989 --> 01:31:47.232
I thought you wanted to know if we'd
ever met... and the answer is no.

1165
01:31:47.292 --> 01:31:49.863
Um, I threatened
to kill him,

1166
01:31:49.928 --> 01:31:54.104
but we were never, what you
might say properly introduced.

1167
01:31:54.165 --> 01:31:58.170
Is it not true that in September
of 1932 you came to Valdosta...

1168
01:31:58.236 --> 01:32:02.082
and took Frank Bennett's wife and
child back to Alabama with you?

1169
01:32:02.140 --> 01:32:04.620
Um... just the wife.
The child came later.

1170
01:32:04.676 --> 01:32:08.146
- How much later?
- The usual. Nine months.

1171
01:32:08.213 --> 01:32:11.092
I suggest
that you bribed...

1172
01:32:11.149 --> 01:32:16.462
this poor, weak woman with
promises of liquor and money,

1173
01:32:16.521 --> 01:32:20.264
and she lost control
of her senses momentarily.

1174
01:32:20.325 --> 01:32:23.329
When her husband came back
to get her and take her home,

1175
01:32:23.395 --> 01:32:28.037
you and your colored man
murdered him in cold blood.

1176
01:32:29.234 --> 01:32:30.838
No, sir.

1177
01:32:30.902 --> 01:32:36.181
Well, where were you on the
night of September 30, 1933?

1178
01:32:36.241 --> 01:32:38.551
I was at the town hall
doing a show.

1179
01:32:38.610 --> 01:32:41.716
- And after that?
- I was at my mother's house.

1180
01:32:41.780 --> 01:32:44.317
Oh, yeah?
Who was with you?

1181
01:32:44.382 --> 01:32:48.728
- Just Big George and myself
- What about your mother? Can she confirm that?

1182
01:32:48.787 --> 01:32:51.063
No, sir.
She died a year ago.

1183
01:32:51.122 --> 01:32:53.625
I'm sorry to hear that.

1184
01:32:53.692 --> 01:32:57.401
But do you expect 12 intelligent
men to believe you,

1185
01:32:57.462 --> 01:33:00.102
although one witness is dead and
the other is a colored man,

1186
01:33:00.165 --> 01:33:03.578
known to be a worthless,
no-good, lying nigger?

1187
01:33:03.635 --> 01:33:05.911
You expect these men
to take your word for it...

1188
01:33:05.971 --> 01:33:08.645
just because
you say so?

1189
01:33:08.707 --> 01:33:13.247
That's right, you gump-faced,
blown-up, baboon-assed bastard!

1190
01:33:13.311 --> 01:33:16.781
One more outburst
like that...

1191
01:33:16.848 --> 01:33:20.352
and I'll hold you in contempt
of court. You understand?

1192
01:33:20.418 --> 01:33:23.228
Yes, sir.

1193
01:33:24.923 --> 01:33:28.496
- Oh, Lord.
- Next witness.

1194
01:33:31.062 --> 01:33:32.541
Did you know that
you were pregnant'...

1195
01:33:32.597 --> 01:33:35.544
at the time
you left Valdosta?

1196
01:33:35.600 --> 01:33:37.546
Yes.

1197
01:33:37.602 --> 01:33:41.209
And yet, you tell us
ave-rand over...

1198
01:33:41.272 --> 01:33:45.846
that you went with this
woman... willingly?

1199
01:33:45.910 --> 01:33:50.120
Yes. I wouldn't raise
my child with Frank Bennett.

1200
01:33:50.181 --> 01:33:52.286
But why?

1201
01:33:52.350 --> 01:33:56.560
- Did this woman promise you money?
- No.

1202
01:33:56.621 --> 01:33:59.192
A bigger home?

1203
01:33:59.257 --> 01:34:02.363
No. No.

1204
01:34:02.427 --> 01:34:05.067
Then tell us,
Mrs. Bennett,

1205
01:34:05.130 --> 01:34:07.667
why would a respectable
Christian woman...

1206
01:34:07.732 --> 01:34:10.542
- go anywhere with this Idgie Threadgoode...
- I object.

1207
01:34:10.602 --> 01:34:12.741
Whose reputation
is known far and wide...

1208
01:34:12.804 --> 01:34:15.045
As a notorious Afar
and drunkard?

1209
01:34:15.106 --> 01:34:17.416
- Objection!
- Sustained!

1210
01:34:20.812 --> 01:34:23.122
Why did you leave...

1211
01:34:23.181 --> 01:34:27.152
with Idgie Threadgoode
that day?

1212
01:34:28.553 --> 01:34:31.864
Answer the question,
Mrs. Bennett.

1213
01:34:32.724 --> 01:34:35.762
Because she-

1214
01:34:38.329 --> 01:34:40.935
She's the best friend
I ever had,

1215
01:34:40.999 --> 01:34:43.104
and I love her.

1216
01:34:43.802 --> 01:34:46.715
Thank you, Mrs. Bennett.
That will be all.

1217
01:34:46.771 --> 01:34:49.615
The defense calls
as its last witness...

1218
01:34:49.674 --> 01:34:52.416
the Rev.
Herbert Scroggins.

1219
01:34:53.745 --> 01:34:56.749
Place your right hand
on the Bible, please.

1220
01:34:56.815 --> 01:35:00.024
I brought my own,
if you don't mind.

1221
01:35:00.085 --> 01:35:04.158
You swear to tell the whole
truth and nothing but the truth?

1222
01:35:04.222 --> 01:35:06.224
I do.

1223
01:35:08.259 --> 01:35:12.503
You have information
about the whereabouts...

1224
01:35:12.564 --> 01:35:16.171
of Idgie Threadgoode and her
colored man, known as Big George,

1225
01:35:16.234 --> 01:35:20.011
on the night
of September 30, 1933?

1226
01:35:20.071 --> 01:35:22.051
Yes, sir,
I do.

1227
01:35:22.107 --> 01:35:24.553
It has been
suggested here...

1228
01:35:24.609 --> 01:35:28.079
that she and her colored man
were at her mother's house.

1229
01:35:28.146 --> 01:35:32.390
- Can you confirm that?
- No, sir. That is a lie.

1230
01:35:32.450 --> 01:35:35.192
Oh, shit.

1231
01:35:35.253 --> 01:35:38.496
It has been my habit
to write all the dates...

1232
01:35:38.556 --> 01:35:41.503
Of the activities of
the church in my Bible.

1233
01:35:41.559 --> 01:35:46.235
I show that the night
of September 30, 1933...

1234
01:35:46.297 --> 01:35:49.335
was the start of our
annual revival...

1235
01:35:49.400 --> 01:35:52.176
down at the
Baptist campground.

1236
01:35:52.237 --> 01:35:54.342
Sister Threadgoode
was there...

1237
01:35:54.405 --> 01:35:58.444
along with her hired man,
George Pullman,

1238
01:35:58.510 --> 01:36:02.652
who was in charge of the
barbecue as he has been...

1239
01:36:02.714 --> 01:36:05.388
- for the last ten years.
- Objection.

1240
01:36:05.450 --> 01:36:09.990
That doesn't mean anything. Murder could've
taken place any time the next couple of clays.

1241
01:36:10.054 --> 01:36:15.094
- Have you ever been to one of our revivals, sir?
- Well, no.

1242
01:36:15.160 --> 01:36:17.231
Do you attend church
regularly, sir?

1243
01:36:17.295 --> 01:36:19.502
'Course I do.

1244
01:36:19.564 --> 01:36:24.104
Good. Well, maybe if you
attended one of our revivals,

1245
01:36:24.169 --> 01:36:26.547
you'd know
they last three days...

1246
01:36:26.604 --> 01:36:28.948
and three nights,
Your Honor.

1247
01:36:31.209 --> 01:36:34.190
Approach the bench.

1248
01:36:34.245 --> 01:36:38.955
Percy, it don't look like
you got a case at all.

1249
01:36:39.017 --> 01:36:41.588
In the first place,
there's no body.

1250
01:36:41.653 --> 01:36:44.930
Second, we got us a preacher
nobody's gonna dispute.

1251
01:36:44.989 --> 01:36:49.199
- But, Your Honor- - I'm tellin'
you. What you got is a lot of nothing.

1252
01:36:49.260 --> 01:36:52.503
I say Frank Bennett
got himself drunk,

1253
01:36:52.564 --> 01:36:56.740
drove into the river and
was long ago eaten up...

1254
01:36:56.801 --> 01:36:59.975
and I don't give
a good goddamn!

1255
01:37:00.038 --> 01:37:03.508
What we got here is a
case of accidental death.

1256
01:37:03.575 --> 01:37:05.213
Case dismissed.

1257
01:37:05.276 --> 01:37:07.722
Whoo!

1258
01:37:14.652 --> 01:37:17.565
See you in church,
Sister?

1259
01:37:18.456 --> 01:37:20.697
Reverend.

1260
01:37:20.758 --> 01:37:25.070
I can't believe he
actually swore on a Bible.

1261
01:37:25.129 --> 01:37:27.075
Well, not really.

1262
01:37:27.131 --> 01:37:29.133
If that judge
had looked closer,

1263
01:37:29.200 --> 01:37:32.272
he'd have seen it was really
a copy of Moby Dick.

1264
01:37:34.305 --> 01:37:38.720
- But why did he do it?
- For the sheer joy of seeing you in church again...

1265
01:37:38.776 --> 01:37:41.620
which I suggested to him
might be your penance.

1266
01:37:41.679 --> 01:37:44.319
- You didn't promise him, did you?
- Yes, ma'am, I did.

1267
01:37:44.382 --> 01:37:46.328
And I never
break my word.

1268
01:37:46.384 --> 01:37:50.764
If I live 1,000 years,
I will never forgive you.

1269
01:37:50.822 --> 01:37:54.998
I don't know what's worse,
church or jail.

1270
01:38:05.970 --> 01:38:09.110
There now.
Don't you look pretty?

1271
01:38:09.173 --> 01:38:11.312
Oh, yes, honey.

1272
01:38:11.376 --> 01:38:16.052
You'll have me lookin' like
Ginger Rogers before you're done.

1273
01:38:16.114 --> 01:38:20.358
Don't let Mr. Dunaway see me.
He's liable to go wild.

1274
01:38:21.853 --> 01:38:25.096
I'm glad to see
you're in a good mood.

1275
01:38:25.156 --> 01:38:28.296
You've slimmed down quite a bit
in the last few weeks.

1276
01:38:28.359 --> 01:38:32.671
I'm just so happy Big George
and Idgie got off.

1277
01:38:32.730 --> 01:38:35.734
I would have killed Frank
Bennett if I could've.

1278
01:38:35.800 --> 01:38:38.337
Did anybody really
think she did it?

1279
01:38:38.403 --> 01:38:41.043
Some said yes,
some said no.

1280
01:38:41.105 --> 01:38:44.245
'Course the only one who really
knew was Frank Bennett.

1281
01:38:44.309 --> 01:38:49.725
And you know what they say.
Dead men tell no tales.

1282
01:38:50.381 --> 01:38:52.691
Towanda-a-a!

1283
01:39:15.974 --> 01:39:19.012
Evelyn, what in the hell
are you doing?

1284
01:39:19.077 --> 01:39:21.990
I need some light
and air.

1285
01:39:22.046 --> 01:39:25.255
Why don't you take one of
your walks or your jog...

1286
01:39:25.316 --> 01:39:28.854
or whatever it is
you do?

1287
01:39:28.920 --> 01:39:31.833
There's no dinner
either!

1288
01:39:31.889 --> 01:39:36.338
Ed, you have any idea why I've
been goin' to all these classes?

1289
01:39:36.394 --> 01:39:39.932
- No.
- I've been trying to save our marriage.

1290
01:39:39.998 --> 01:39:42.035
What's the point
of my tryin'...

1291
01:39:42.100 --> 01:39:46.776
if you're gonna sit on
your butt drinking beer...

1292
01:39:46.838 --> 01:39:49.682
and watching baseball,
basketball, football...

1293
01:39:49.741 --> 01:39:52.881
bowling and hockey
and golf...

1294
01:39:52.944 --> 01:39:56.824
and Challenge
of the Gladiators?

1295
01:40:02.520 --> 01:40:07.060
Mrs. Couch, I'm Sue,
Mrs. Otis' daughter-in-law.

1296
01:40:07.125 --> 01:40:10.572
How are you? I've heard about
you from Mrs. Threadgoode.

1297
01:40:10.628 --> 01:40:14.337
She is so sweet. She's been
lookin' after my mother-in-law.

1298
01:40:14.399 --> 01:40:17.175
Now, how is Mrs. Otis doin', by the way?

1299
01:40:17.235 --> 01:40:21.706
Much better, thank you. It takes
time getting used to a strange place.

1300
01:40:21.773 --> 01:40:25.812
I'm glad to hear it. Mrs.
Threadgoode's been anxious to get home.

1301
01:40:25.877 --> 01:40:30.087
Mrs. Couch, Mrs. Threadgoode
doesn't have a house anymore.

1302
01:40:30.148 --> 01:40:33.618
- They tore that down.
- What?

1303
01:40:33.684 --> 01:40:37.928
They had to. It was falling
apart, and it was condemned.

1304
01:40:37.989 --> 01:40:40.936
Oh, no.

1305
01:40:40.992 --> 01:40:45.202
- Does she know that?
- No, well, we didn't see any point in telling her.

1306
01:40:45.263 --> 01:40:47.766
It would just break her heart,
poor old thing

1307
01:40:47.832 --> 01:40:51.780
But I am so glad
I got a chance to meet you.

1308
01:40:51.836 --> 01:40:55.045
You take care of yourself now.
Bye-bye.

1309
01:42:05.009 --> 01:42:07.319
Oh, Evelyn. hey!

1310
01:42:07.378 --> 01:42:09.858
Hey-

1311
01:42:09.914 --> 01:42:12.292
Do you like
my roses?

1312
01:42:12.350 --> 01:42:15.695
Since I can't get home
to look at my own roses...

1313
01:42:15.753 --> 01:42:18.131
I made myself
a paper garden.

1314
01:42:18.189 --> 01:42:21.693
- Got everything but the bugs.
- They're lovely.

1315
01:42:21.759 --> 01:42:25.036
- You been here long?
- Happy birthday!

1316
01:42:25.096 --> 01:42:27.599
- Oh!
- I shouldn't have woken you up.

1317
01:42:27.665 --> 01:42:31.943
'Course you should've. Don't you never let
me sleep through a visitor's day, honey.

1318
01:42:32.003 --> 01:42:36.748
- I look forward to them all week.
- So do I, Mrs. Threadgoode.

1319
01:42:36.807 --> 01:42:40.152
Oh! I can't believe
you remembered.

1320
01:42:40.211 --> 01:42:44.421
You made me
fried green tomatoes!

1321
01:42:46.851 --> 01:42:48.888
Mmm!
They're delicious.

1322
01:42:48.953 --> 01:42:52.298
- It's your recipe. Are they cold?
- No. They're just the way...

1323
01:42:52.356 --> 01:42:56.634
- we used to have 'em at the Whistle Stop Cafe.
- Mmm!

1324
01:42:56.694 --> 01:43:00.642
You couldn't be sweeter to me
if you was my own daughter.

1325
01:43:00.698 --> 01:43:02.871
Here's your napkin.

1326
01:43:02.934 --> 01:43:04.971
And wait-wait-wait.

1327
01:43:05.036 --> 01:43:07.607
Queen, queen.

1328
01:43:10.775 --> 01:43:14.917
You know,
I don't feel 83.

1329
01:43:14.979 --> 01:43:19.121
It sorta slipped up on me.

1330
01:43:21.219 --> 01:43:24.666
I never expected
to live this long.

1331
01:43:24.722 --> 01:43:30.331
'Course, the Lord takes us home
when he wants us.

1332
01:43:39.337 --> 01:43:42.978
Are you all right?

1333
01:43:43.040 --> 01:43:45.384
I was thinking
about Ruth.

1334
01:43:45.443 --> 01:43:48.253
After the trial
was over,

1335
01:43:48.312 --> 01:43:50.519
Everything went back
to normal...

1336
01:43:50.581 --> 01:43:54.358
till that fall
when Ruth lost her appetite.

1337
01:43:54.418 --> 01:43:56.989
By the time Doc Hadley
looked at her,

1338
01:43:57.054 --> 01:44:01.264
he said the cancer was so bad
she only had a couple of weeks.

1339
01:44:01.325 --> 01:44:04.067
Well, we moved her
to the Threadgoode house...

1340
01:44:04.128 --> 01:44:08.975
and put her downstairs
so she'd be more comfortable.

1341
01:44:09.033 --> 01:44:13.539
Sipsey moved in with her
and never left her side.

1342
01:44:13.604 --> 01:44:15.743
Hold on, baby
I'm right here.

1343
01:44:15.806 --> 01:44:20.482
Idgie just prayed
for a miracle.

1344
01:44:39.764 --> 01:44:43.234
Now, listen to me.

1345
01:44:43.301 --> 01:44:45.838
Make sure he graduates.

1346
01:44:45.903 --> 01:44:50.113
And don't... let him
come to the funeral.

1347
01:44:50.174 --> 01:44:52.848
I don't want him going
through that mess.

1348
01:44:52.910 --> 01:44:56.221
Would you quit talkin'
like that?

1349
01:44:56.280 --> 01:44:58.783
What funeral?

1350
01:44:58.849 --> 01:45:01.227
You're gonna be back on
your feet feelin' just fine...

1351
01:45:01.285 --> 01:45:03.959
in just a few days.

1352
01:45:04.021 --> 01:45:06.934
Just you wait.

1353
01:45:06.991 --> 01:45:10.131
Oh, what's the matter,
son?

1354
01:45:15.966 --> 01:45:19.641
Well,
let's go for a walk.

1355
01:45:20.338 --> 01:45:21.942
Did you get
into a fight?

1356
01:45:22.006 --> 01:45:24.714
I got punched
in the nose.

1357
01:45:24.775 --> 01:45:28.279
I can't play
like everyone else.

1358
01:45:28.346 --> 01:45:31.884
Did I ever tell you the
story about... the oysters?

1359
01:45:31.949 --> 01:45:34.429
All the millions of 'em
just lying around-

1360
01:45:34.485 --> 01:45:39.332
- And God put sand in one of 'em, and it makes a pearl.
- Oh.

1361
01:45:41.092 --> 01:45:43.766
Did I ever tell you about
Eva's three-legged dog?

1362
01:45:43.828 --> 01:45:45.933
How it never felt sorry
for itself...

1363
01:45:45.996 --> 01:45:49.637
and howl ought to be smarter than a
dumb dog and not feel sorry for myself.

1364
01:45:51.435 --> 01:45:54.780
You listen to everything
I say, don't you?

1365
01:45:54.839 --> 01:45:57.820
You get real mad at me
when I don't.

1366
01:45:57.875 --> 01:45:59.582
Well,

1367
01:46:02.046 --> 01:46:05.050
you know about
your mama.

1368
01:46:05.116 --> 01:46:07.619
She's sick.

1369
01:46:07.685 --> 01:46:09.722
Mm-hmm.

1370
01:46:11.255 --> 01:46:14.702
See, now is the time
for courage.

1371
01:46:14.759 --> 01:46:18.468
I guess you already know
that there are...

1372
01:46:18.529 --> 01:46:21.533
angels masqueradin' as people
walkin' around this planet,

1373
01:46:21.599 --> 01:46:24.773
and your mom's
the bravest one of those.

1374
01:46:29.039 --> 01:46:31.144
Come here.

1375
01:46:38.849 --> 01:46:41.261
Mama, I can hit!
You should see me.

1376
01:46:41.318 --> 01:46:44.128
Idgie, she hit me in
the back with a curveball.

1377
01:46:44.188 --> 01:46:46.361
I didn't duck,
and I hardly cried.

1378
01:46:46.424 --> 01:46:49.894
She hit you?

1379
01:46:49.960 --> 01:46:53.965
Well, she did that
to me once too,

1380
01:46:54.031 --> 01:46:56.807
but I think
I did cry.

1381
01:46:58.702 --> 01:47:02.673
Mama, I'm sorry
if you're sad.

1382
01:47:02.740 --> 01:47:05.050
Well,

1383
01:47:05.109 --> 01:47:08.215
give me a big kiss then,
and I'll never be sad again.

1384
01:47:15.753 --> 01:47:18.666
And you best not be sad
neither.

1385
01:47:18.722 --> 01:47:21.965
You understand?

1386
01:47:22.026 --> 01:47:23.972
You promise?

1387
01:47:24.028 --> 01:47:26.065
Promise.

1388
01:47:26.130 --> 01:47:30.078
Attaboy.
You go and wash up.

1389
01:47:53.891 --> 01:47:55.928
Sweet baby.

1390
01:47:59.897 --> 01:48:03.174
You two
be alone now.

1391
01:48:03.868 --> 01:48:07.543
Hey, girl.

1392
01:48:10.040 --> 01:48:12.111
No.

1393
01:48:14.044 --> 01:48:17.116
That's nice.

1394
01:48:18.115 --> 01:48:21.824
Will you do one thing
for me?

1395
01:48:21.886 --> 01:48:25.493
- Yeah, anything.
- Be good to yourself.

1396
01:48:25.556 --> 01:48:28.503
Even...

1397
01:48:28.559 --> 01:48:31.096
settle down if
you can find someone...

1398
01:48:31.161 --> 01:48:33.903
who can beat you
in poker.

1399
01:48:41.605 --> 01:48:46.577
There's so many things
I want to say to you.

1400
01:48:46.644 --> 01:48:49.181
No.

1401
01:48:50.014 --> 01:48:52.688
I love your stories.

1402
01:48:52.750 --> 01:48:55.697
Tell me a story,
Idgie.

1403
01:48:58.556 --> 01:49:02.402
Oh, God.

1404
01:49:02.459 --> 01:49:05.565
Go on,
you old' bee charmer.

1405
01:49:05.629 --> 01:49:09.304
Tell me
a good tall tale.

1406
01:49:10.701 --> 01:49:14.410
Tell me the one
about the lake.

1407
01:49:15.706 --> 01:49:20.348
- What lake?
- The one... that used to be here.

1408
01:49:22.479 --> 01:49:24.425
Oh.

1409
01:49:26.483 --> 01:49:30.056
Well, that was
just a lie.

1410
01:49:30.120 --> 01:49:32.896
I know that, fool.

1411
01:49:32.957 --> 01:49:35.028
Tell me anyway.

1412
01:49:35.092 --> 01:49:38.505
Tell me the story.

1413
01:49:40.064 --> 01:49:43.511
Well...

1414
01:49:45.536 --> 01:49:48.016
one time...

1415
01:49:48.072 --> 01:49:50.882
there was this lake.

1416
01:49:55.312 --> 01:49:59.692
And, uh, it was
right outside of town.

1417
01:49:59.750 --> 01:50:05.200
We used to go fishin' and
swimmin' and canoein' in it.

1418
01:50:05.255 --> 01:50:08.498
And see,
one November...

1419
01:50:08.559 --> 01:50:10.869
this big flock of ducks...

1420
01:50:10.928 --> 01:50:15.968
came in and landed
on that lake and, uh,

1421
01:50:16.033 --> 01:50:20.880
and then the temperature dropped so fast
that the lake just froze right there.

1422
01:50:20.938 --> 01:50:23.214
And the, uh,

1423
01:50:23.273 --> 01:50:27.050
the ducks, they...

1424
01:50:27.111 --> 01:50:31.287
flew off, you see,
and took that lake with 'em.

1425
01:50:31.348 --> 01:50:34.591
And, uh.

1426
01:50:34.652 --> 01:50:39.658
Now they say that lake is
somewhere over in Georgia.

1427
01:50:39.723 --> 01:50:42.795
Can you imagine?

1428
01:51:40.484 --> 01:51:43.761
It's all right,
honey.

1429
01:51:43.821 --> 01:51:49.802
Let her go.

1430
01:51:49.860 --> 01:51:54.104
You know,
Miss Ruth was a lady.

1431
01:51:54.164 --> 01:51:57.441
And a lady
always knows...

1432
01:51:57.501 --> 01:52:00.505
when to leave.

1433
01:52:06.009 --> 01:52:10.116
When I think on our
departed sister, Ruth Jamison,

1434
01:52:10.180 --> 01:52:13.286
I'm reminded of our
Lord's Sermon on the Mount...

1435
01:52:13.350 --> 01:52:15.830
and how his teachings-

1436
01:52:15.886 --> 01:52:20.335
It's funny how strong
Ruth affected everyone.

1437
01:52:20.390 --> 01:52:23.803
even Smokey Lonesome.

1438
01:52:23.861 --> 01:52:26.535
When he died
a few years back...

1439
01:52:26.597 --> 01:52:29.305
he had one possession
on him,

1440
01:52:29.366 --> 01:52:31.972
A picture of Ruth.

1441
01:52:33.337 --> 01:52:37.444
He was in love with her
from the first time he saw her.

1442
01:52:37.508 --> 01:52:40.387
We all were.

1443
01:52:46.350 --> 01:52:48.830
I shouldn't
a- told you this.

1444
01:52:50.754 --> 01:52:54.725
I hate death.
It scares me so.

1445
01:52:54.792 --> 01:52:57.329
Death is nothin'
to be afraid of!

1446
01:52:57.394 --> 01:53:00.466
Look at me. I'm at
the jumpin'- off place,

1447
01:53:00.531 --> 01:53:03.774
and I ain't afraid
one bit.

1448
01:53:03.834 --> 01:53:07.543
Oh, Ninny,
you're so brave.

1449
01:53:09.106 --> 01:53:13.054
Ruth and Idgie were brave,
not me.

1450
01:53:13.110 --> 01:53:16.489
I wouldn't be afraid
of death if I was you.

1451
01:53:16.547 --> 01:53:21.496
I'd be more afraid of driving
in rush-hour traffic.

1452
01:55:16.700 --> 01:55:19.704
Hi, honey.
Look what I got you.

1453
01:55:19.770 --> 01:55:21.807
Ah...

1454
01:55:21.872 --> 01:55:25.342
Ed, how sweet!

1455
01:55:25.409 --> 01:55:27.855
- Lilies! My favorite.
- Yeah.

1456
01:55:27.911 --> 01:55:31.051
I know.
Sometimes I even amaze myself.

1457
01:55:31.114 --> 01:55:35.221
- What's the occasion?
- Oh, honey, I just...

1458
01:55:35.285 --> 01:55:38.266
feel sorry about
the past few months.

1459
01:55:38.322 --> 01:55:42.327
I don't know what you're really
up to and what's going on with you,

1460
01:55:42.392 --> 01:55:46.807
but I guess I could've been more helpful
with your job and everything, you know.

1461
01:55:48.031 --> 01:55:49.908
Well, why are you...

1462
01:55:49.967 --> 01:55:52.948
puttin' up this wall
where you just tore one down?

1463
01:55:53.003 --> 01:55:56.143
Well...
I changed my mind.

1464
01:55:56.206 --> 01:55:58.982
I don't mean to seem
dense or anything,

1465
01:55:59.042 --> 01:56:03.286
- but what's changed?
- The air and the light.

1466
01:56:05.649 --> 01:56:08.255
- Ed-
- Hmm?

1467
01:56:08.318 --> 01:56:10.798
You remember how
you used to tell me...

1468
01:56:10.854 --> 01:56:13.596
you always wanted
two women in your house?

1469
01:56:13.657 --> 01:56:15.967
Oh, God.

1470
01:56:16.026 --> 01:56:17.699
Yeah.

1471
01:56:17.761 --> 01:56:19.798
Well...

1472
01:56:19.863 --> 01:56:22.810
what if I was
the younger of the two?

1473
01:56:22.866 --> 01:56:26.404
I don't believe
I get your drift.

1474
01:56:26.470 --> 01:56:31.010
I want something more than I've
ever wanted anything before.

1475
01:56:31.074 --> 01:56:33.850
I want to bring
Mrs. Threadgoode...

1476
01:56:33.910 --> 01:56:36.117
to our home.

1477
01:56:36.179 --> 01:56:38.819
I want her
to live here with us.

1478
01:56:38.882 --> 01:56:41.385
I want to give her the love
she's given me.

1479
01:56:41.451 --> 01:56:45.627
You're kiddin' me, aren't you?
I'm absolutely serious.

1480
01:56:45.689 --> 01:56:50.536
That's why I'm puttin' the
wall to Kyle's room back up.

1481
01:56:50.594 --> 01:56:53.666
Well, honey, this isn't
something you're just go and do.

1482
01:56:53.730 --> 01:56:56.404
I mean,
she's an old woman.

1483
01:56:56.466 --> 01:56:59.709
What if she got sick?
Who's gonna take care of her?

1484
01:56:59.770 --> 01:57:01.477
I will!

1485
01:57:01.538 --> 01:57:03.540
I can't leave her
in that place.

1486
01:57:03.607 --> 01:57:07.521
She's not a stray cat.
Hell, she isn't even family.

1487
01:57:07.577 --> 01:57:10.649
- She's family to me.
- Now, Evelyn.

1488
01:57:11.481 --> 01:57:14.553
Evelyn?

1489
01:57:14.618 --> 01:57:16.495
Honey?

1490
01:57:16.553 --> 01:57:18.555
Ah, look...

1491
01:57:18.622 --> 01:57:22.866
have you mentioned this
harebrained idea to her?

1492
01:57:22.926 --> 01:57:25.998
- Not yet.
- Well, good!

1493
01:57:26.063 --> 01:57:28.543
Then we'll just pretend
it never happened.

1494
01:57:28.598 --> 01:57:31.636
I'm making my own money.
I'll pay for everything.

1495
01:57:31.701 --> 01:57:35.274
You don't have to do
a thing.

1496
01:57:35.338 --> 01:57:37.841
Evelyn...

1497
01:57:37.908 --> 01:57:40.388
it's never
gonna happen.

1498
01:57:40.444 --> 01:57:43.118
So just forget
about it.

1499
01:57:44.714 --> 01:57:47.490
Don't you ever
say "never" to me.

1500
01:57:56.426 --> 01:57:59.236
Someone helped put a mirror
up in front of my face,

1501
01:57:59.296 --> 01:58:01.902
and I didn't like
what I saw one bit.

1502
01:58:01.965 --> 01:58:05.811
You know what I did?
I changed.

1503
01:58:05.869 --> 01:58:09.783
And that someone...
was Mrs. Threadgoode.

1504
01:58:09.840 --> 01:58:14.346
She needs my love and care,
and I'm gonna give it to her.

1505
01:58:16.113 --> 01:58:19.754
If you'll excuse me,
I have to go to the gym.

1506
01:58:24.688 --> 01:58:27.726
And if you won't listen
to reason...

1507
01:58:27.791 --> 01:58:31.432
there's always Towanda.

1508
01:58:46.209 --> 01:58:49.190
Hey, Nin-

1509
01:58:51.848 --> 01:58:54.886
What are you doing?

1510
01:58:54.951 --> 01:58:57.693
Those are her things,
Mrs. Threadgoode's things!

1511
01:58:57.754 --> 01:59:00.860
- What are you doing in here? Where's Mrs. Threadgoode?
- Who?

1512
01:59:00.924 --> 01:59:03.768
Mrs. Threadgoode! The woman
who lives here. Are you deaf?

1513
01:59:03.827 --> 01:59:06.740
I'm sorry, miss.
All they told me...

1514
01:59:06.796 --> 01:59:11.006
was that the woman who lived
in here died this morning.

1515
01:59:12.869 --> 01:59:15.008
Oh. my God!

1516
01:59:15.071 --> 01:59:19.417
Wha- What
are you sayin'?

1517
01:59:19.476 --> 01:59:21.649
She died early
this morning.

1518
01:59:21.711 --> 01:59:26.057
They were shorthanded so they asked
me to take all this stuff down.

1519
01:59:26.116 --> 01:59:28.619
That? all I know.

1520
01:59:48.004 --> 01:59:49.950
Stop that!

1521
01:59:50.006 --> 01:59:52.384
What is the matter
with you people?

1522
01:59:52.442 --> 01:59:55.389
Can't you wait a goddamn day,
for Chrissake?

1523
01:59:55.445 --> 01:59:58.449
Do you have no respect?
These are her things!

1524
01:59:58.515 --> 02:00:02.691
I'm sorry, but they told me to get
this room ready for another patient.

1525
02:00:02.752 --> 02:00:05.961
She may be just
another patient to you,

1526
02:00:06.022 --> 02:00:10.129
- but she was my friend, and I loved her.
- I'm sorry.

1527
02:00:10.193 --> 02:00:12.139
I'm just
following orders.

1528
02:00:12.195 --> 02:00:15.142
- What is going on?
- Why didn't you call me?

1529
02:00:15.198 --> 02:00:18.543
- You could've called me before
you sent that idiot- - I'm sorry.

1530
02:00:18.602 --> 02:00:21.276
It never occurred to me that
you would take it this hard.

1531
02:00:21.338 --> 02:00:24.979
- I didn't even get to tell
her good-bye. - Oh, I know.

1532
02:00:25.041 --> 02:00:29.012
These things are difficult, but
she died peacefully in her sleep.

1533
02:00:29.079 --> 02:00:32.356
To tell you the truth, I thought
you'd be happy for Mrs. Threadgoode.

1534
02:00:32.415 --> 02:00:35.453
- Happy?
- Why, yes! This is what she wanted.

1535
02:00:35.518 --> 02:00:37.464
What?
To be dead?

1536
02:00:37.520 --> 02:00:40.057
No, to go home.
You just missed her.

1537
02:00:40.123 --> 02:00:42.569
She left in a yellow cab
about a half hour ago.

1538
02:00:42.626 --> 02:00:45.334
I don't understand.
What? A cab?

1539
02:00:45.395 --> 02:00:49.673
She said there wasn't no reason for
her to stay now that Mrs. Otis had died.

1540
02:00:49.733 --> 02:00:52.373
Mrs...

1541
02:00:52.435 --> 02:00:54.608
Otis is dead?

1542
02:00:54.671 --> 02:00:58.551
Oh, Mrs. Otis died.

1543
02:00:58.608 --> 02:01:00.610
Mrs. Otis died!

1544
02:01:00.677 --> 02:01:03.886
Mrs. Otis!
Oh, God!

1545
02:01:03.947 --> 02:01:07.986
Not that... I'm glad that
Mrs. Otis died, it's just-

1546
02:01:08.051 --> 02:01:10.691
Oh, God.
I've gotta stop her.

1547
02:01:50.126 --> 02:01:53.369
Hey, Evelyn,
somebody stole my house.

1548
02:01:53.430 --> 02:01:56.343
It was right here
when I left.

1549
02:01:56.399 --> 02:02:01.178
Unless
- Oh, Evelyn, you don't reckon I'm crazy, do you?

1550
02:02:01.237 --> 02:02:05.447
- It was here when I left.
- No, honey, you're not crazy.

1551
02:02:05.508 --> 02:02:08.284
This is the place.

1552
02:02:08.345 --> 02:02:12.384
Why would anyone want to
steal an old lady's home?

1553
02:02:12.449 --> 02:02:14.588
Wasn't worth nothin'.

1554
02:02:14.651 --> 02:02:18.064
Oh, honey,
nobody stole it.

1555
02:02:18.121 --> 02:02:22.001
They had to tear it down.
It was condemned.

1556
02:02:22.058 --> 02:02:24.197
I'm sorry.
I shoulda told you.

1557
02:02:24.260 --> 02:02:27.537
Well, somebody
shoulda told me.

1558
02:02:27.597 --> 02:02:32.444
- I'm old. I'm not a child.
- I'm sorry.

1559
02:02:32.502 --> 02:02:35.847
My husband Cleo and I
lived in this house...

1560
02:02:35.905 --> 02:02:38.408
for more than 40 years.

1561
02:02:38.475 --> 02:02:41.888
Now, it's... it's gone.

1562
02:02:41.945 --> 02:02:45.518
83 years worth of livin'
and all that's left of me...

1563
02:02:45.582 --> 02:02:49.621
is what's in this box, a
bunch of old cards and pictures.

1564
02:02:49.686 --> 02:02:52.166
Come on.
I'll take you home.

1565
02:02:52.222 --> 02:02:54.361
This is my home!

1566
02:02:54.424 --> 02:02:56.426
And now it's gone.

1567
02:02:56.493 --> 02:02:59.030
And Mrs. Otis
is gone.

1568
02:02:59.095 --> 02:03:01.200
I...

1569
02:03:01.264 --> 02:03:03.870
I don't quite
know what to do.

1570
02:03:03.933 --> 02:03:07.779
This is the first time I can remember
when I don't have a soul to look after.

1571
02:03:07.837 --> 02:03:10.215
You can come
look after me and Ed.

1572
02:03:10.273 --> 02:03:12.583
Oh, you're sweet,

1573
02:03:12.642 --> 02:03:15.452
but I think you're doin'
just fine on your own.

1574
02:03:15.512 --> 02:03:19.824
Don't you know you'd be
like a gift for us?

1575
02:03:19.883 --> 02:03:23.057
You're the reason
I get up every morning...

1576
02:03:23.119 --> 02:03:26.464
and that Mary Kay's
havin' such a good year...

1577
02:03:26.523 --> 02:03:31.097
and I don't look like some
blob from a horror movie.

1578
02:03:31.161 --> 02:03:35.200
Well,with a little help
from Idgie and Ruth.

1579
02:03:36.766 --> 02:03:39.303
Come on. I've got
your room all ready.

1580
02:03:39.369 --> 02:03:41.781
What does Ed say
about all this?

1581
02:03:41.838 --> 02:03:45.684
He'll learn
to love it.

1582
02:03:49.145 --> 02:03:53.287
Did I ever tell you that Mrs.
Otis was Sipsey's baby sister?

1583
02:03:53.349 --> 02:03:56.023
- No, ma'am.
- Yes, she was.

1584
02:03:56.085 --> 02:03:59.965
Mrs. Otis was with Sipsey
and me the night Sipsey died.

1585
02:04:00.023 --> 02:04:05.200
Sipsey told me a story that night
I've never told a living soul, Evelyn.

1586
02:04:05.261 --> 02:04:08.401
A story about
what really happened...

1587
02:04:08.465 --> 02:04:11.810
The night Frank Bennett
disappeared

1588
02:04:44.367 --> 02:04:47.905
- Hey there!
- You got to come quick.

1589
02:04:47.971 --> 02:04:52.943
- The show has hardly begun.
- You got to come quick. You hear me?

1590
02:04:58.848 --> 02:05:01.454
- Run, get help! Run, quick!
- Where's the baby?

1591
02:05:01.518 --> 02:05:03.327
Never mind.

1592
02:05:22.038 --> 02:05:23.711
Excuse me, sir.

1593
02:05:23.773 --> 02:05:29.280
I don't believe you should be
goin' anywhere with Ruth's baby.

1594
02:05:40.924 --> 02:05:43.666
Like I said,
you ain't goin' nowhere.

1595
02:05:43.726 --> 02:05:46.297
Damn, you a thickheaded
son-of-a-bitch, ain't you?

1596
02:05:50.500 --> 02:05:52.480
I told you...

1597
02:05:52.535 --> 02:05:56.984
you ain't goin' nowheres
with Miss Ruth's baby.

1598
02:06:02.612 --> 02:06:04.819
Come on, angel.
Come on.

1599
02:06:04.881 --> 02:06:08.727
Come on, sweetheart.
It's all right.

1600
02:06:08.785 --> 02:06:11.288
Come on.
It's all right, baby.

1601
02:06:14.190 --> 02:06:16.932
it was self-defense.

1602
02:06:16.993 --> 02:06:21.840
I don't know why any white
jury would care why I did it.

1603
02:06:21.898 --> 02:06:24.708
- Well, I saw it, and I can testify.
- Excuse me here.

1604
02:06:24.767 --> 02:06:26.940
I don't mean
no offense here,

1605
02:06:27.003 --> 02:06:30.075
but I don't know who's less
likely to convince a jury,

1606
02:06:30.139 --> 02:06:32.415
my mama...
or Mr. Smokey.

1607
02:06:32.475 --> 02:06:35.285
No offense taken.

1608
02:06:35.345 --> 02:06:37.757
You're a good man,
Mr. Smokey.

1609
02:06:37.814 --> 02:06:41.853
- You did good.
- The sun's almost up.

1610
02:06:45.388 --> 02:06:48.767
- George?
- Mm-hmm?

1611
02:06:48.825 --> 02:06:51.601
I think...

1612
02:06:51.661 --> 02:06:55.199
it's hog-boiling time.

1613
02:06:55.264 --> 02:06:57.540
No, ma'am. It
ain't cold enough.

1614
02:06:57.600 --> 02:07:00.376
It's hog-boiling time.

1615
02:07:03.306 --> 02:07:05.252
Big George?

1616
02:07:05.308 --> 02:07:08.414
- Uh-huh? - When is that
barbecue gonna be ready?

1617
02:07:08.478 --> 02:07:10.822
It's gonna be ready
any time now.

1618
02:07:10.880 --> 02:07:15.795
Smells so damn good I just
can't wait to get me some.

1619
02:07:15.852 --> 02:07:20.164
- Now, don't you forget to call me when that's ready.
- All right.

1620
02:07:33.903 --> 02:07:36.179
Here you go.

1621
02:07:37.740 --> 02:07:41.381
- Miss Idgie? Smokey left town.
- Yeah?

1622
02:07:41.444 --> 02:07:45.449
I thought it'd be best
under the circumstances.

1623
02:07:45.515 --> 02:07:49.486
He asked that
you tell Ruth good-bye.

1624
02:07:49.552 --> 02:07:52.032
Shame he had to go.

1625
02:07:58.995 --> 02:08:03.910
Hold on! I'm comin'.

1626
02:08:08.771 --> 02:08:11.547
- What you want?
- We want some barbecue.

1627
02:08:11.607 --> 02:08:15.316
Not today you don't.
Go on.

1628
02:08:28.357 --> 02:08:31.497
Why, this is about the
best barbecue I ever ate!

1629
02:08:32.995 --> 02:08:36.499
The secret's
in the sauce.

1630
02:08:45.274 --> 02:08:49.154
Sipsey?
My God!

1631
02:08:49.212 --> 02:08:53.558
That fryin' pan did more
than fry chicken that night.

1632
02:08:55.318 --> 02:08:59.789
Did Idgie really barbecue Frank
Bennett? Are you pullin' my leg?

1633
02:08:59.856 --> 02:09:03.565
Secret's in the sauce,
or so I've been told.

1634
02:09:07.063 --> 02:09:10.909
Now you know why
Idgie had to go on trial.

1635
02:09:10.967 --> 02:09:14.608
She knew the law would never
believe Sipsey. No!

1636
02:09:14.670 --> 02:09:17.173
Sipsey or Big George
or anyone else of color...

1637
02:09:17.240 --> 02:09:20.710
would've been hangin'
from the nearest tree.

1638
02:09:20.777 --> 02:09:23.053
To this day,
I'm still not sure...

1639
02:09:23.112 --> 02:09:25.683
whether Ruth
ever believed...

1640
02:09:25.748 --> 02:09:29.890
that Idgie didn't kill
Frank Bennett.

1641
02:09:29.952 --> 02:09:34.196
Truth's a funny thing
sometimes.

1642
02:09:34.257 --> 02:09:38.228
- I feel better now.
- Good.

1643
02:09:38.294 --> 02:09:41.605
I feel better 'cause
all these people'll live...

1644
02:09:41.664 --> 02:09:44.736
as long as
you remember 'em.

1645
02:09:44.801 --> 02:09:46.747
You reminded me...

1646
02:09:46.803 --> 02:09:50.216
about what the most
important thing in life is.

1647
02:09:50.273 --> 02:09:52.617
- Do you know what I think it is?
- No, ma'am.

1648
02:09:52.675 --> 02:09:55.952
Friends.
Best friends.

1649
02:09:56.012 --> 02:09:59.050
Oh. Ninny!

1650
02:10:00.216 --> 02:10:01.957
Look.

1651
02:10:07.223 --> 02:10:09.066
Oh!

1652
02:10:28.277 --> 02:10:30.223
Idgie?

1653
02:10:33.683 --> 02:10:37.563
- Idgie's alive?
- Oh, yes!

1654
02:10:37.620 --> 02:10:41.898
She's still out and about
Charmin' bees and selling honey.

1655
02:10:41.958 --> 02:10:45.929
Sometimes I think
I catch a glimpse of her.

1656
02:10:51.834 --> 02:10:54.280
Maybe we'll
see her today.

1657
02:10:54.337 --> 02:10:56.977
Maybe.

1658
02:10:58.641 --> 02:11:01.349
Let's go.

1659
02:11:12.855 --> 02:11:17.167
After Ruth died and
the railroad stopped runnin',

1660
02:11:17.226 --> 02:11:21.231
the cafe shut down, and everybody
just scattered to the winds.

1661
02:11:22.565 --> 02:11:25.944
It was never more than just
a little knockabout place.

1662
02:11:26.002 --> 02:11:28.812
But now that
I look back on it,

1663
02:11:28.871 --> 02:11:31.147
when that cafe closed...

1664
02:11:31.207 --> 02:11:35.314
the heart of the town
just stopped beating.

1665
02:11:35.378 --> 02:11:38.222
It's funny how
a little place like this...

1666
02:11:38.281 --> 02:11:42.127
brought so many people together.

